Module microservice.py.

Class and functions to help communication between PumpWood like systems.

  42def break_in_chunks(df_to_break: pd.DataFrame, chunksize: int = 1000):
  43    """Break a dataframe in chunks of chunksize."""
  44    to_return = list()
  45    for g, df in df_to_break.groupby(np.arange(len(df_to_break)) // chunksize):
  46        to_return.append(df)
  47    return to_return

  50class PumpWoodMicroService():
  51    """Class to define an inter-pumpwood MicroService."""
  52
  53    @staticmethod
  54    def _ajust_server_url(server_url):
  55        if server_url is None:
  56            return None
  57        if server_url[-1] != '/':
  58            return server_url + '/'
  59        else:
  60            return server_url
  61
  62    def __init__(self, name: str = None, server_url: str = None,
  63                 username: str = None, password: str = None,
  64                 verify_ssl: bool = True, auth_suffix: str = None,
  65                 debug: bool = None):
  66        """
  67        Create new PumpWoodMicroService object.
  68
  69        Creates a new microservice object. If just name is passed, object must
  70        be initiate after with init() method.
  71
  72        Args:
  73            name (str): Name of the microservice, helps when exceptions
  74                        are raised.
  75        Kwargs:
  76            server_url (str): url of the server that will be connected.
  77            username (str): Username that will be logged on.
  78            password (str): Variable to be converted to JSON and posted along
  79            with the request
  80            verify_ssl (bool): Set if microservice will verify ssl certificate
  81        Returns:
  82            PumpWoodMicroService: New PumpWoodMicroService object
  83        Raises:
  84            No particular Raises
  85        Example:
  86            No example
  87        """
  88        self.name = name
  89        self.__headers = None
  90        self.__user = None
  91        self.__username = username
  92        self.__password = password
  93        self.server_url = self._ajust_server_url(server_url)
  94        self.verify_ssl = verify_ssl
  95        self.__base_header = {'Content-Type': 'application/json'}
  96        self.__auth_header = None
  97        self.__token_expiry = None
  98        self.auth_suffix = auth_suffix
  99        self.debug = debug
 100        self.is_mfa_login = False
 101
 102    def init(self, name: str, server_url: str, username: str,
 103             password: str, verify_ssl: bool = True, auth_suffix: str = None,
 104             debug: bool = None):
 105        """
 106        Start a microservice after creation.
 107
 108        Usefull in flask app config.
 109
 110        Args:
 111            name (str): Name of the microservice, helps when exceptions
 112                        are raised.
 113            server_url (str): url of the server that will be connected.
 114            user_name (str): Username that will be logged on.
 115            password (str): Variable to be converted to JSON and posted along
 116            with the request
 117            verify_ssl (bool): Set if microservice will verify ssl certificate
 118        Kwargs:
 119            auth_suffix (str): Add a suffix to auth end-point in case of
 120                authentication end-point have any suffix.
 121        Returns:
 122            No return
 123        Raises:
 124            No particular Raises
 125        Example:
 126            No example
 127        """
 128        self.name = name
 129        self.__headers = None
 130        self.__username = username
 131        self.__password = password
 132        self.server_url = self._ajust_server_url(server_url)
 133        self.verify_ssl = verify_ssl
 134        self.auth_suffix = auth_suffix
 135        self.debug = debug
 136
 137    @staticmethod
 138    def angular_json(request_result):
 139        """
 140        Convert text to Json removing any XSSI at the beging of JSON.
 141
 142        Args:
 143            request_result (Request): JSON Request to be converted
 144        Kwargs:
 145            No Kwargs
 146        Returns:
 147            No return
 148        Raises:
 149            No particular Raises
 150        Example:
 151            No example
 152        """
 153        if request_result.text == '':
 154            return None
 155
 156        string_start = ")]}',\n"
 157        try:
 158            if request_result.text[:6] == string_start:
 159                return (json.loads(request_result.text[6:]))
 160            else:
 161                return (json.loads(request_result.text))
 162        except Exception:
 163            return {"error": "Can not decode to Json",
 164                    'msg': request_result.text}
 165
 166    def time_to_expiry(self) -> pd.Timedelta:
 167        """
 168        Return time to token expiry.
 169
 170        Args:
 171            No Args.
 172        Kwargs:
 173            No Kwargs.
 174        Return:
 175            Return time until token expiration.
 176        """
 177        if self.__token_expiry is None:
 178            return None
 179
 180        now_datetime = pd.to_datetime(datetime.datetime.utcnow(), utc=True)
 181        time_to_expiry = self.__token_expiry - now_datetime
 182        return time_to_expiry
 183
 184    def is_credential_set(self) -> bool:
 185        """
 186        Check if username and password are set on object.
 187
 188        Args:
 189            No Args.
 190        Kwargs:
 191            No Kwargs.
 192        Return:
 193            True if usename and password were set during object creation or
 194            later with init function.
 195        """
 196        return not (self.__username is None or self.__password is None)
 197
 198    def login(self, force_refresh: bool = False) -> None:
 199        """
 200        Log microservice in using username and password provided.
 201
 202        Args:
 203            No Args.
 204        Kwargs:
 205            force_refresh [bool]: Force token refresh despise still valid
 206                according to self.__token_expiry.
 207        Returns:
 208            No return
 209        Raises:
 210            Exception: If login response has status diferent from 200.
 211        Example:
 212            No example
 213
 214        """
 215        if not self.is_credential_set():
 216            raise PumpWoodUnauthorized(
 217                message="Microservice username or/and password not set")
 218
 219        # Check if expiry time is 1h from now
 220        refresh_expiry = False
 221        if self.__token_expiry is None:
 222            refresh_expiry = True
 223        else:
 224            time_to_expiry = self.time_to_expiry()
 225            if time_to_expiry < datetime.timedelta(hours=1):
 226                refresh_expiry = True
 227
 228        # When if debug always refresh token
 229        is_debug = None
 230        if self.debug is None:
 231            is_debug = os.getenv("DEBUG", "FALSE") == "TRUE"
 232        else:
 233            is_debug = self.debug
 234
 235        if refresh_expiry or force_refresh or is_debug:
 236            login_url = None
 237            if self.auth_suffix is None:
 238                login_url = urljoin(
 239                    self.server_url, 'rest/registration/login/')
 240            else:
 241                temp_url = 'rest/{suffix}registration/login/'.format(
 242                    suffix=self.auth_suffix.lower())
 243                login_url = urljoin(self.server_url, temp_url)
 244
 245            login_result = requests.post(
 246                login_url, json={
 247                    'username': self.__username,
 248                    'password': self.__password},
 249                verify=self.verify_ssl)
 250
 251            login_data = {}
 252            try:
 253                login_data = PumpWoodMicroService.angular_json(login_result)
 254                login_result.raise_for_status()
 255            except Exception as e:
 256                raise PumpWoodUnauthorized(
 257                    message="Login not possible.\nError: " + str(e),
 258                    payload=login_data)
 259
 260            if 'mfa_token' in login_data.keys():
 261                login_data = self.confirm_mfa_code(mfa_login_data=login_data)
 262
 263            self.__auth_header = {
 264                'Authorization': 'Token ' + login_data['token']}
 265            self.__user = login_data["user"]
 266            self.__token_expiry = pd.to_datetime(login_data['expiry'])
 267
 268    def confirm_mfa_code(self, mfa_login_data: dict) -> dict:
 269        """
 270        Ask user to confirm MFA code to login.
 271
 272        Args:
 273            mfa_login_data [dict]: Result from login request with 'mfa_token'
 274                as key.
 275        Return [dict]:
 276            Return login returned with MFA confimation.
 277        Raise:
 278            Raise error if reponse is not valid.
 279        """
 280        code = input("## Please enter MFA code: ")
 281        url = urljoin(
 282            self.server_url, 'rest/registration/mfa-validate-code/')
 283        mfa_response = requests.post(url, headers={
 284            "X-PUMPWOOD-MFA-Autorization": mfa_login_data['mfa_token']},
 285            json={"mfa_code": code})
 286        self.error_handler(mfa_response)
 287
 288        # Set is_mfa_login true to indicate that login required MFA
 289        self.is_mfa_login = True
 290        return PumpWoodMicroService.angular_json(mfa_response)
 291
 292    def logout(self, auth_header: dict = None) -> bool:
 293        """
 294        Logout token.
 295
 296        Args:
 297            No args.
 298        Kwards:
 299            auth_header [dict] Authentication header.
 300        Return [bool]:
 301            True if logout was ok.
 302        """
 303        resp = self.request_post(
 304            url='rest/registration/logout/',
 305            data={}, auth_header=auth_header)
 306        return resp is None

 308    def logout_all(self, auth_header: dict = None) -> bool:
 309        """
 310        Logout all tokens from user.
 311
 312        Args:
 313            No args.
 314        Kwards:
 315            auth_header [dict] Authentication header.
 316        Return [bool]:
 317            True if logout all was ok.
 318        """
 319        resp = self.request_post(
 320            url='rest/registration/logoutall/',
 321            data={}, auth_header=auth_header)
 322        return resp is None

 324    def set_auth_header(self, auth_header: dict,
 325                        token_expiry: pd.Timestamp) -> None:
 326        """
 327        Set auth_header and token_expiry date.
 328
 329        Args:
 330            auth_header [dict]: Authentication header to be set.
 331            token_expiry [pd.Timestamp]: Token expiry datetime to be set.
 332        Return [None]:
 333            No return.
 334        """
 335        self.__auth_header = auth_header
 336        self.__token_expiry = pd.to_datetime(token_expiry, utc=True)

 338    def get_auth_header(self) -> dict:
 339        """
 340        Retrieve auth_header and token_expiry from object.
 341
 342        Args:
 343            No Args.
 344        Kwargs:
 345            No Kwargs.
 346        Return:
 347            Return authorization header and token_expiry datetime from object.
 348        """
 349        return {
 350            "auth_header": self.__auth_header,
 351            "token_expiry": self.__token_expiry}

 353    def check_if_logged(self, auth_header: dict) -> bool:
 354        """
 355        Check if user is logged.
 356
 357        Args:
 358            auth_header (dict): AuthHeader to substitute the
 359                microservice original
 360        Return [bool]:
 361            Return True if auth_header is looged and False if not
 362        """
 363        try:
 364            check = self.request_get(
 365                url="rest/registration/check/", auth_header=auth_header)
 366        except PumpWoodUnauthorized:
 367            return False
 368        return check

 370    def get_user_info(self, auth_header: dict = None) -> dict:
 371        """
 372        Get user info.
 373
 374        Args:
 375            No Args:
 376
 377        Return [dict]:
 378            A serialized user object with information of the logged user.
 379        """
 380        user_info = self.request_get(
 381            url="rest/registration/retrieveauthenticateduser/",
 382            auth_header=auth_header)
 383        return user_info
 384
 385    def _check__auth_header(self, auth_header, multipart: bool = False):
 386        """
 387        Check if auth_header is set or auth_header if provided.
 388
 389        Args:
 390            auth_header (dict): AuthHeader to substitute the
 391                                microservice original
 392        Kwargs:
 393            No Kwargs
 394        Returns:
 395            dict: Return a header dict to be used in requests.
 396        Raises:
 397            PumpWoodUnauthorized: If microservice is not logged and a
 398                                  auth_header method argument is not provided.
 399            PumpWoodUnauthorized: If microservice is logged and a auth_header
 400                                  method argument is provided.
 401        Example:
 402            No example
 403
 404        """
 405        if auth_header is None:
 406            # Login will refresh token if it is 1h to expire, it will also
 407            # check if credentials are set.
 408            self.login()
 409            temp__auth_header = self.__auth_header.copy()
 410            if multipart:
 411                return temp__auth_header
 412            else:
 413                temp__auth_header.update(self.__base_header)
 414                return temp__auth_header
 415        else:
 416            if self.is_credential_set():
 417                msg_tmp = (
 418                    'MicroService {name} already looged and '
 419                    'auth_header was provided')
 420                raise PumpWoodUnauthorized(
 421                    msg_tmp.format(name=self.name))
 422
 423            # Set base header as JSON since unserialization is done using
 424            # Pumpwood Communication serialization funciton
 425            temp__auth_header = auth_header.copy()
 426            if multipart:
 427                return temp__auth_header
 428            else:
 429                temp__auth_header.update(self.__base_header)
 430                return temp__auth_header
 431
 432    def error_handler(cls, response):
 433        """
 434        Handle request error.
 435
 436        Check if is a Json and propagate the error with
 437        same type if possible. If not Json raises the content.
 438
 439        Arg:
 440            response (Response): response to be handled.
 441        Kwargs:
 442            No kwargs.
 443        Returns:
 444            No return.
 445        Raises:
 446            Exception: If content-type is not application/json.
 447            Exception: If content-type is application/json, but type not
 448                       present or not recognisable.
 449            Other Exception: If content-type is application/json if type is
 450                             present and recognisable.
 451        Example:
 452            No example
 453
 454        """
 455        if not response.ok:
 456            utcnow = datetime.datetime.utcnow()
 457            response_content_type = response.headers['content-type']
 458
 459            # Request information
 460            url = response.url
 461            method = response.request.method
 462            if 'application/json' not in response_content_type.lower():
 463                # Raise the exception as first in exception deep.
 464                exception_dict = [{
 465                    "exception_url": url,
 466                    "exception_method": method,
 467                    "exception_utcnow": utcnow.isoformat(),
 468                    "exception_deep": 1}]
 469                raise PumpWoodOtherException(
 470                    message=response.text, payload={
 471                        "!exception_stack!": exception_dict})
 472
 473            # Build error stack
 474            response_dict = PumpWoodMicroService.angular_json(response)
 475
 476            # Removing previus error stack
 477            payload = deepcopy(response_dict.get("payload", {}))
 478            exception_stack = deepcopy(payload.pop("!exception_stack!", []))
 479
 480            exception_deep = len(exception_stack)
 481            exception_dict = {
 482                "exception_url": url,
 483                "exception_method": method,
 484                "exception_utcnow": utcnow.isoformat(),
 485                "exception_deep": exception_deep + 1
 486            }
 487            exception_stack.insert(0, exception_dict)
 488            payload["!exception_stack!"] = exception_stack
 489
 490            # Propagate error
 491            exception_message = response_dict.get("message", "")
 492            exception_type = response_dict.get("type", None)
 493            if exception_type is not None:
 494                raise exceptions_dict[exception_type](
 495                    message=exception_message,
 496                    status_code=response.status_code,
 497                    payload=payload)
 498            else:
 499                is_invalid_token = cls.is_invalid_token_response(response)
 500                response_dict["!exception_stack!"] = exception_stack
 501                if is_invalid_token:
 502                    raise PumpWoodUnauthorized(
 503                        message="Invalid token.",
 504                        payload=response.json())
 505                else:
 506                    raise PumpWoodOtherException(
 507                        message="Not mapped exception JSON",
 508                        payload=response_dict)
 509
 510    @classmethod
 511    def is_invalid_token_response(cls,
 512                                  response: requests.models.Response) -> bool:
 513        """
 514        Check if reponse has invalid token error.
 515
 516        Args:
 517            response [requests.models.Response]: Request reponse to check for
 518                invalid token.
 519        Return [bool]:
 520            Return True if response has an invalid token status.
 521        """
 522        if response.status_code == 401:
 523            return True
 524        return False
 525
 526    def request_post(self, url: str, data: any, files: list = None,
 527                     auth_header: dict = None, parameters: dict = {}):
 528        """
 529        Make a POST a request to url with data as Json payload.
 530
 531        Args:
 532            url (str): Url to make the request.
 533            data (any); Data to be used as Json payload.
 534        Kwargs:
 535            files(list of tuples): A list of tuples with
 536                                   (file name, [file1, file2, ...]).
 537            params [dict]: Url parameters.
 538            auth_header(dict): Auth data to overhide microservice's.
 539        Returns:
 540            any: Return the post result
 541        Raises:
 542            Response is passed to error_handler function.
 543        Example:
 544            No example
 545
 546        """
 547        # If parameters are not none convert them to json before
 548        # sending information on query string, 'True' is 'true' on javascript
 549        # for exemple
 550        if parameters is not None:
 551            parameters = copy.deepcopy(parameters)
 552            for key in parameters.keys():
 553                # Do not convert str to json, it put extra "" araound string
 554                if type(parameters[key]) is not str:
 555                    parameters[key] = pumpJsonDump(parameters[key])
 556
 557        response = None
 558        if files is None:
 559            request_header = self._check__auth_header(auth_header=auth_header)
 560            post_url = urljoin(self.server_url, url)
 561            response = requests.post(
 562                url=post_url, data=pumpJsonDump(data),
 563                params=parameters, verify=self.verify_ssl,
 564                headers=request_header)
 565
 566            # Retry request if token is not valid forcing token renew
 567            retry_with_login = (
 568                self.is_invalid_token_response(response) and
 569                auth_header is None)
 570            if retry_with_login:
 571                self.login(force_refresh=True)
 572                request_header = self._check__auth_header(
 573                    auth_header=auth_header)
 574                response = requests.post(
 575                    url=post_url, data=pumpJsonDump(data),
 576                    params=parameters, verify=self.verify_ssl,
 577                    headers=request_header)
 578
 579        # Request with files are done using multipart serializing all fields
 580        # as json
 581        else:
 582            request_header = self._check__auth_header(
 583                auth_header=auth_header, multipart=True)
 584            post_url = urljoin(self.server_url, url)
 585            temp_data = {'__json__': pumpJsonDump(data)}
 586            response = requests.post(
 587                url=post_url, data=temp_data, files=files, params=parameters,
 588                verify=self.verify_ssl, headers=request_header)
 589
 590            retry_with_login = (
 591                self.is_invalid_token_response(response) and
 592                auth_header is None)
 593            if retry_with_login:
 594                self.login(force_refresh=True)
 595                request_header = self._check__auth_header(
 596                    auth_header=auth_header)
 597                response = requests.post(
 598                    url=post_url, data=temp_data, files=files,
 599                    params=parameters, verify=self.verify_ssl,
 600                    headers=request_header)
 601
 602        # Handle errors and re-raise if Pumpwood Exceptions
 603        self.error_handler(response)
 604
 605        # Check if reponse is a file
 606        headers = response.headers
 607        content_disposition = headers.get('content-disposition')
 608        if content_disposition is not None:
 609            file_name = re.findall('filename=(.+)', content_disposition)
 610            if len(file_name) == 1:
 611                return {
 612                    "__file_name__": file_name[0],
 613                    "__content__": response.content}
 614            else:
 615                return {
 616                    "__file_name__": None,
 617                    "__content__": response.content}
 618        else:
 619            return PumpWoodMicroService.angular_json(response)
 620
 621    def request_get(self, url, parameters: dict = {},
 622                    auth_header: dict = None):
 623        """
 624        Make a GET a request to url with data as Json payload.
 625
 626        Args:
 627            url (str): Url to make the request.
 628        Kwargs:
 629            parameters (dict): Url parameters to make the request.
 630            auth_header (dict): Authentication dictionary.
 631        Returns:
 632            any: Return the post result
 633        Raises:
 634            Response is passed to error_handler function.
 635        Example:
 636            No example
 637        """
 638        request_header = self._check__auth_header(auth_header)
 639
 640        # If parameters are not none convert them to json before
 641        # sending information on query string, 'True' is 'true' on javascript
 642        # for example
 643        if parameters is not None:
 644            parameters = copy.deepcopy(parameters)
 645            for key in parameters.keys():
 646                # Do not convert str to json, it put extra "" araound string
 647                if type(parameters[key]) is not str:
 648                    parameters[key] = pumpJsonDump(parameters[key])
 649
 650        get_url = urljoin(self.server_url, url)
 651        response = requests.get(
 652            get_url, verify=self.verify_ssl, headers=request_header,
 653            params=parameters)
 654
 655        retry_with_login = (
 656            self.is_invalid_token_response(response) and
 657            auth_header is None)
 658        if retry_with_login:
 659            self.login(force_refresh=True)
 660            request_header = self._check__auth_header(auth_header=auth_header)
 661            response = requests.get(
 662                get_url, verify=self.verify_ssl, headers=request_header,
 663                params=parameters)
 664
 665        # Re-raise Pumpwood exceptions
 666        self.error_handler(response=response)
 667
 668        json_types = ["application/json", "application/json; charset=utf-8"]
 669        if response.headers['content-type'] in json_types:
 670            return PumpWoodMicroService.angular_json(response)
 671        else:
 672            d = response.headers['content-disposition']
 673            fname = re.findall("filename=(.+)", d)[0]
 674
 675            return {
 676                "content": response.content,
 677                "content-type": response.headers['content-type'],
 678                "filename": fname}
 679
 680    def request_delete(self, url, parameters: dict = None,
 681                       auth_header: dict = None):
 682        """
 683        Make a DELETE a request to url with data as Json payload.
 684
 685        Args:
 686            url (str): Url to make the request.
 687        Kwargs:
 688            parameters (dict): Dictionary with Urls parameters.
 689            auth_header (dict): Auth header if microservice not logged.
 690        Returns:
 691            any: Return the post result
 692        Raises:
 693            Response is passed to error_handler function.
 694        Example:
 695            No example
 696        """
 697        request_header = self._check__auth_header(auth_header)
 698
 699        post_url = self.server_url + url
 700        response = requests.delete(
 701            post_url, verify=self.verify_ssl, headers=request_header,
 702            params=parameters)
 703
 704        # Retry request if token is not valid forcing token renew
 705        retry_with_login = (
 706            self.is_invalid_token_response(response) and
 707            auth_header is None)
 708        if retry_with_login:
 709            self.login(force_refresh=True)
 710            request_header = self._check__auth_header(auth_header=auth_header)
 711            response = requests.delete(
 712                post_url, verify=self.verify_ssl, headers=request_header,
 713                params=parameters)
 714
 715        # Re-raise Pumpwood Exceptions
 716        self.error_handler(response)
 717        return PumpWoodMicroService.angular_json(response)
 718
 719    def list_registered_routes(self, auth_header: dict = None):
 720        """List routes that have been registed at Kong."""
 721        list_url = None
 722        if self.auth_suffix is None:
 723            list_url = 'rest/pumpwood/routes/'
 724        else:
 725            list_url = 'rest/{suffix}pumpwood/routes/'.format(
 726                suffix=self.auth_suffix.lower())
 727        routes = self.request_get(
 728            url=list_url, auth_header=auth_header)
 729        for key, item in routes.items():
 730            item.sort()
 731        return routes
 732
 733    def is_microservice_registered(self, microservice: str,
 734                                   auth_header: dict = None) -> bool:
 735        """
 736        List routes that have been registed at Kong.
 737
 738        Args:
 739            microservice [str]: Service associated with microservice
 740                registered on Pumpwood Kong.
 741        Kwargs:
 742            No Kwargs.
 743        Return:
 744            Return true if microservice is registered.
 745        """
 746        routes = self.list_registered_routes(auth_header=auth_header)
 747        return microservice in routes.keys()

 761    def dummy_call(self, payload: dict = None,
 762                   auth_header: dict = None) -> dict:
 763        """
 764        Return a dummy call to ensure headers and payload reaching app.
 765
 766        Args:
 767            No args.
 768        Kwards:
 769            payload (dict]): Payload to be returned by the dummy call
 770                end-point.
 771            auth_header (dict): Auth header if microservice not logged.
 772
 773        Return:
 774            Return a dictonary with:
 775            - full_path (dict): Full path of the request.
 776            - method (dict): Method used at the call
 777            - headers (dict): Headers at the request.
 778            - data (dict): Post payload sent at the request.
 779        """
 780        list_url = None
 781        if self.auth_suffix is None:
 782            list_url = 'rest/pumpwood/dummy-call/'
 783        else:
 784            list_url = 'rest/{suffix}pumpwood/dummy-call/'.format(
 785                suffix=self.auth_suffix.lower())
 786
 787        if payload is None:
 788            return self.request_get(
 789                url=list_url, auth_header=auth_header)
 790        else:
 791            return self.request_post(
 792                url=list_url, data=payload,
 793                auth_header=auth_header)
 794
 795    def dummy_raise(self, exception_class: str, exception_deep: int,
 796                    payload: dict = {}, auth_header: dict = None) -> None:
 797        """
 798        Raise an Pumpwood error with the payload.
 799
 800        Can be used for debug purposes.
 801
 802        Args:
 803            exception_class (str): Class of the exception to be raised.
 804            exception_deep (int): Deep of the exception in microservice
 805                calls.
 806        Kwards:
 807            payload (dict]): Payload to be returned by the dummy call
 808                end-point.
 809            auth_header (dict): Auth header if microservice not logged.
 810        Return:
 811            Should not return any results, all possible call should result
 812            in raising the correspondent error.
 813        Exceptions:
 814            Should raise the correspondent error passed on exception_class
 815            arg, with payload.
 816        """
 817        url = 'rest/pumpwood/dummy-raise/'
 818        payload["exception_class"] = exception_class
 819        payload["exception_deep"] = exception_deep
 820        self.request_post(url=url, data=payload, auth_header=auth_header)
 821
 822    def get_pks_from_unique_field(self, model_class: str, field: str,
 823                                  values: List[Any]) -> pd.DataFrame:
 824        """
 825        Get pk using unique fields values.
 826
 827        Use unique field values to retrieve pk of the objects.
 828
 829        Args:
 830            model_class [str]: Model class of the objects.
 831            field [str]: Unique field to fetch pk.
 832            values [List[Any]]: List of the unique fields used to fetch
 833                primary keys.
 834        Return [pd.DataFrame]:
 835            Return a dataframe in same order as values with columns:
 836                - pk: correspondent primary key of the unique value.
 837                - [field]: Column with same name of field argument,
 838                    correspondent to pk.
 839        """
 840        is_dimension_tag = 'dimensions->' in field
 841        if not is_dimension_tag:
 842            fill_options = self.fill_options(model_class=model_class)
 843            field_details = fill_options.get(field)
 844            if field_details is None:
 845                msg = (
 846                    "Field is not a dimension tag and not found on model "
 847                    "fields. Field [{field}]")
 848                raise PumpWoodQueryException(
 849                    message=msg, payload={"field": field})
 850
 851            is_unique_field = field_details.get("unique", False)
 852            if not is_unique_field:
 853                msg = "Field [{}] to get pk from is not unique"
 854                raise PumpWoodQueryException(
 855                    message=msg, payload={"field": field})
 856
 857        filter_dict = {field + "__in": list(set(values))}
 858        pk_map = None
 859        if not is_dimension_tag:
 860            list_results = pd.DataFrame(self.list_without_pag(
 861                model_class=model_class, filter_dict=filter_dict,
 862                fields=["pk", field]), columns=["pk", field])
 863            pk_map = list_results.set_index(field)["pk"]
 864
 865        # If is dimension tag, fetch dimension and unpack it
 866        else:
 867            dimension_tag = field.split("->")[1]
 868            list_results = pd.DataFrame(self.list_without_pag(
 869                model_class=model_class, filter_dict=filter_dict,
 870                fields=["pk", "dimensions"]))
 871            pk_map = {}
 872            if len(list_results) != 0:
 873                pk_map = list_results\
 874                    .pipe(unpack_dict_columns, columns=["dimensions"])\
 875                    .set_index(dimension_tag)["pk"]
 876
 877        values_series = pd.Series(values)
 878        return pd.DataFrame({
 879            "pk": values_series.map(pk_map).values,
 880            field: values_series
 881        })
 882
 883    @staticmethod
 884    def _build_list_url(model_class: str):
 885        return "rest/%s/list/" % (model_class.lower(),)

 887    def list(self, model_class: str, filter_dict: dict = {},
 888             exclude_dict: dict = {}, order_by: list = [],
 889             auth_header: dict = None, fields: list = None,
 890             default_fields: bool = False, limit: int = None,
 891             foreign_key_fields: bool = False,
 892             **kwargs) -> list:
 893        """
 894        List objects with pagination.
 895
 896        Function to post at list end-point (resumed data) of PumpWood like
 897        systems, results will be paginated. To get next pag, send recived pk at
 898        exclude dict (ex.: exclude_dict={id__in: [1,2,...,30]}).
 899
 900        Args:
 901          model_class (str): Model class of the end-point
 902          filter_dict (dict): Filter dict to be used at the query
 903            (objects.filter arguments).
 904          exclude_dict (dict):  Exclude dict to be used at the query
 905            (objects.exclude arguments).
 906          order_by (list): Ordering list to be used at the query
 907            (objects.order_by arguments).
 908          auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.
 909          fields(list[str]): Select the fields to be returned by the list
 910            end-point.
 911          default_fields [bool]: Return the fields specified at
 912              self.list_fields.
 913          limit [int]: Set the limit of elements of the returned query.
 914          foreign_key_fields [bool]: Return forenging key objects.
 915
 916        Returns:
 917          list: Contaiing objects serialized by list Serializer.
 918
 919        Raises:
 920          No especific raises.
 921
 922        Example:
 923          No example yet.
 924
 925        """
 926        url_str = self._build_list_url(model_class)
 927        post_data = {
 928            'filter_dict': filter_dict, 'exclude_dict': exclude_dict,
 929            'order_by': order_by, 'default_fields': default_fields,
 930            'limit': limit, 'foreign_key_fields': foreign_key_fields}
 931        if fields is not None:
 932            post_data["fields"] = fields
 933        return self.request_post(
 934            url=url_str, data=post_data, auth_header=auth_header)
 935
 936    def list_by_chunks(self, model_class: str, filter_dict: dict = {},
 937                       exclude_dict: dict = {}, auth_header: dict = None,
 938                       fields: list = None, default_fields: bool = False,
 939                       chunk_size: int = 50000, **kwargs) -> list:
 940        """
 941        List object fetching them by chucks using pk to paginate.
 942
 943        List data by chunck to load by datasets without breaking the backend
 944        or receive server timeout. It load chunks orderring the results using
 945        id of the tables, it can be changed but it should be unique otherwise
 946        unexpected results may occur.
 947
 948        Args:
 949          model_class (str): Model class of the end-point
 950
 951        Kwargs:
 952          filter_dict (dict) = {}: Filter dict to be used at the query
 953            (objects.filter arguments).
 954          exclude_dict (dict) = {}:  Exclude dict to be used at the query
 955            (objects.exclude arguments).
 956          auth_header (dict) = None: Dictionary containing the auth header.
 957          fields (list[str]) = None: Select the fields to be returned by the
 958            list end-point.
 959          default_fields (bool) = False: Return the fields specified at
 960              self.list_fields.
 961          chuck_size [int]: Number of objects to be fetched each query.
 962
 963        Returns:
 964          list: Contaiing objects serialized by list Serializer.
 965
 966        Raises:
 967          No especific raises.
 968
 969        Example:
 970          No example yet.
 971
 972        """
 973        copy_filter_dict = copy.deepcopy(filter_dict)
 974
 975        list_all_results = []
 976        max_order_col = 0
 977        while True:
 978            print("- fetching chunk [{}]".format(max_order_col))
 979            copy_filter_dict["pk__gt"] = max_order_col
 980            temp_results = self.list(
 981                model_class=model_class, filter_dict=copy_filter_dict,
 982                exclude_dict=exclude_dict, order_by=["pk"],
 983                auth_header=auth_header, fields=fields,
 984                default_fields=default_fields, limit=chunk_size)
 985
 986            # Break if results is empty
 987            if len(temp_results) == 0:
 988                break
 989
 990            max_order_col = temp_results[-1]["pk"]
 991            list_all_results.extend(temp_results)
 992
 993        return list_all_results
 994
 995    @staticmethod
 996    def _build_list_without_pag_url(model_class: str):
 997        return "rest/%s/list-without-pag/" % (model_class.lower(),)
 998
 999    def list_without_pag(self, model_class: str, filter_dict: dict = {},
1000                         exclude_dict: dict = {}, order_by: list = [],
1001                         auth_header: dict = None, return_type: str = 'list',
1002                         convert_geometry: bool = True, fields: list = None,
1003                         default_fields: bool = False,
1004                         foreign_key_fields: bool = False, **kwargs):
1005        """
1006        List object without pagination.
1007
1008        Function to post at list end-point (resumed data) of PumpWood like
1009        systems, results won't be paginated.
1010        **Be carefull with large returns.**
1011
1012        Args:
1013          model_class (str): Model class of the end-point
1014
1015        Kwargs:
1016          filter_dict (dict): Filter dict to be used at the query
1017            (objects.filter arguments)
1018          exclude_dict (dict):  Exclude dict to be used at the query
1019            (objects.exclude arguments)
1020          order_by (list): Ordering list to be used at the query
1021            (objects.order_by arguments)
1022          auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.
1023          return_type(str): Set the return type, can be [list, dataframe].
1024          convert_geometry(bool) = True: Covert geometry to shapely.
1025          fields(list[str]): Select the fields to be returned by the list
1026            end-point.
1027          default_fields [bool]: Return the fields specified at
1028              self.list_fields.
1029          foreign_key_fields [bool]: Return forenging key objects.
1030        Returns:
1031          list: Contaiing objects serialized by list Serializer.
1032
1033        Raises:
1034          No especific raises.
1035
1036        Example:
1037          No example yet.
1038
1039        """
1040        url_str = self._build_list_without_pag_url(model_class)
1041        post_data = {
1042            'filter_dict': filter_dict, 'exclude_dict': exclude_dict,
1043            'order_by': order_by, 'default_fields': default_fields,
1044            'foreign_key_fields': foreign_key_fields}
1045
1046        if fields is not None:
1047            post_data["fields"] = fields
1048        results = self.request_post(
1049            url=url_str, data=post_data, auth_header=auth_header)
1050
1051        ##################################################
1052        # Converting geometry to Shapely objects in Python
1053        geometry_in_results = False
1054        if convert_geometry:
1055            for obj in results:
1056                geometry_value = obj.get("geometry")
1057                if geometry_value is not None:
1058                    obj["geometry"] = geometry.shape(geometry_value)
1059                    geometry_in_results = True
1060        ##################################################
1061
1062        if return_type == 'list':
1063            return results
1064        elif return_type == 'dataframe':
1065            if (model_class.lower() == "descriptiongeoarea") and \
1066                    geometry_in_results:
1067                return geopd.GeoDataFrame(results, geometry='geometry')
1068            else:
1069                return pd.DataFrame(results)
1070        else:
1071            raise Exception("return_type must be 'list' or 'dataframe'")
1072

1212    @staticmethod
1213    def _build_retrieve_file_url(model_class: str, pk: int):
1214        return "rest/%s/retrieve-file/%s/" % (model_class.lower(), pk)
1215
1216    def retrieve_file(self, model_class: str, pk: int, file_field: str,
1217                      auth_header: dict = None, save_file: bool = True,
1218                      save_path: str = "./", file_name: str = None,
1219                      if_exists: str = "fail"):
1220        """
1221        Retrieve a file from PumpWood.
1222
1223        Args:
1224          model_class (str): Class of the model to retrieve file.
1225          pk (int): Pk of the object associeted file.
1226          file_field (str): Field of the file to be downloaded.
1227        Kwargs:
1228          auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.
1229          save_file (bool): If data is to be saved as file or return get
1230            response.
1231          save_path (str): Path of the directory to save file.
1232          file_name (str): Name of the file, if None it will have same name as
1233                saved in PumpWood.
1234          if_exists {'fail', 'change_name', 'overwrite', 'skip'}: Set what to
1235            do if there is a file with same name. Skip will not download file
1236            if there is already with same os.path.join(save_path, file_name),
1237            file_name must be set for skip argument.
1238        Returns:
1239          requset.response or str
1240        Raises:
1241          No especific raises.
1242        Example:
1243          No example yet.
1244
1245        """
1246        if if_exists not in ["fail", "change_name", "overwrite", "skip"]:
1247            raise PumpWoodException(
1248                "if_exists must be in ['fail', 'change_name', 'overwrite', "
1249                "'skip']")
1250
1251        if file_name is not None and if_exists == 'skip':
1252            file_path = os.path.join(save_path, file_name)
1253            is_file_already = os.path.isfile(file_path)
1254            if is_file_already:
1255                print("skiping file already exists: ", file_path)
1256                return file_path
1257
1258        url_str = self._build_retrieve_file_url(model_class=model_class, pk=pk)
1259        file_response = self.request_get(
1260            url=url_str, parameters={"file-field": file_field},
1261            auth_header=auth_header)
1262        if not save_file:
1263            return file_response
1264
1265        if not os.path.exists(save_path):
1266            raise PumpWoodException(
1267                "Path to save retrieved file [{}] does not exist".format(
1268                    save_path))
1269
1270        file_name = secure_filename(file_name or file_response["filename"])
1271        file_path = os.path.join(save_path, file_name)
1272        is_file_already = os.path.isfile(file_path)
1273        if is_file_already:
1274            if if_exists == "change_name":
1275                filename, file_extension = os.path.splitext(file_path)
1276                too_many_tries = True
1277                for i in range(10):
1278                    new_path = "{filename}__{count}{extension}".format(
1279                        filename=filename, count=i,
1280                        extension=file_extension)
1281                    if not os.path.isfile(new_path):
1282                        file_path = new_path
1283                        too_many_tries = False
1284                        break
1285                if too_many_tries:
1286                    raise PumpWoodException(
1287                        ("Too many tries to find a not used file name." +
1288                         " file_path[{}]".format(file_path)))
1289
1290            elif if_exists == "fail":
1291                raise PumpWoodException(
1292                    ("if_exists set as 'fail' and there is a file with same" +
1293                     "name. file_path [{}]").format(file_path))
1294
1295        with open(file_path, "wb") as file:
1296            file.write(file_response["content"])
1297        return file_path
1298
1299    @staticmethod
1300    def _build_retrieve_file_straming_url(model_class: str, pk: int):
1301        return "rest/%s/retrieve-file-streaming/%s/" % (
1302            model_class.lower(), pk)
1303
1304    def retrieve_streaming_file(self, model_class: str, pk: int,
1305                                file_field: str, file_name: str,
1306                                auth_header: dict = None,
1307                                save_path: str = "./",
1308                                if_exists: str = "fail"):
1309        """
1310        Retrieve a file from PumpWood.
1311
1312        Args:
1313          model_class (str): Class of the model to retrieve file.
1314          pk (int): Pk of the object associeted file.
1315          file_field (str): Field of the file to be downloaded.
1316          file_name (str): Name of the file, if None it will have same name as
1317                saved in PumpWood.
1318
1319        Kwargs:
1320          auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.
1321          save_path (str): Path of the directory to save file.
1322          if_exists {'fail', 'change_name', 'overwrite'}: Set what to do if
1323            there is a file with same name.
1324
1325        Returns:
1326          requset.response or str
1327
1328        Raises:
1329          No especific raises.
1330
1331        Example:
1332          No example yet.
1333        """
1334        request_header = self._check__auth_header(auth_header)
1335
1336        # begin Args check
1337        if if_exists not in ["fail", "change_name", "overwrite"]:
1338            raise PumpWoodException(
1339                "if_exists must be in ['fail', 'change_name', 'overwrite']")
1340
1341        if not os.path.exists(save_path):
1342            raise PumpWoodException(
1343                "Path to save retrieved file [{}] does not exist".format(
1344                    save_path))
1345        # end Args check
1346
1347        file_path = os.path.join(save_path, file_name)
1348        if os.path.isfile(file_path) and if_exists == "change_name":
1349            filename, file_extension = os.path.splitext(file_path)
1350            too_many_tries = False
1351            for i in range(10):
1352                new_path = "{filename}__{count}{extension}".format(
1353                    filename=filename, count=i,
1354                    extension=file_extension)
1355                if not os.path.isfile(new_path):
1356                    file_path = new_path
1357                    too_many_tries = True
1358                    break
1359            if not too_many_tries:
1360                raise PumpWoodException(
1361                    ("Too many tries to find a not used file name." +
1362                     " file_path[{}]".format(file_path)))
1363
1364        if os.path.isfile(file_path) and if_exists == "fail":
1365            raise PumpWoodException(
1366                ("if_exists set as 'fail' and there is a file with same" +
1367                 "name. file_path [{}]").format(file_path))
1368
1369        url_str = self._build_retrieve_file_straming_url(
1370            model_class=model_class, pk=pk)
1371
1372        get_url = self.server_url + url_str
1373        with requests.get(
1374                get_url, verify=self.verify_ssl, headers=request_header,
1375                params={"file-field": file_field}) as response:
1376            self.error_handler(response)
1377            with open(file_path, 'wb') as f:
1378                for chunk in response.iter_content(chunk_size=8192):
1379                    if chunk:
1380                        f.write(chunk)
1381        return file_path
1382
1383    @staticmethod
1384    def _build_save_url(model_class):
1385        return "rest/%s/save/" % (model_class.lower())
1386
1387    def save(self, obj_dict, files: dict = None, auth_header: dict = None):
1388        """
1389        Save or Update a new object.
1390
1391        Function to save or update a new model_class object. If obj_dict{'pk'}
1392        is None or not defined a new object will be created. The obj
1393        model class is defided at obj_dict['model_class'] and if not defined an
1394        PumpWoodObjectSavingException will be raised.
1395
1396        Args:
1397          obj_dict (dict): Model data dictionary. It must have 'model_class'
1398                           key and if 'pk' key is not defined a new object will
1399                           be created, else object with pk will be updated.
1400        Kwargs:
1401          files (dict): A dictionary of files to be added to as a multi-part
1402                        post request.
1403          auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.
1404        Returns:
1405          dict: Updated/Created object data.
1406        Raises:
1407          PumpWoodObjectSavingException(
1408              'To save an object obj_dict must have model_class defined.'):
1409            Will be raised if model_class key is not present on
1410            obj_dict dictionary
1411        Example:
1412          No example yet.
1413
1414        """
1415        model_class = obj_dict.get('model_class')
1416        if model_class is None:
1417            raise PumpWoodObjectSavingException(
1418                'To save an object obj_dict must have model_class defined.')
1419
1420        url_str = self._build_save_url(model_class)
1421        return self.request_post(
1422            url=url_str, data=obj_dict, files=files,
1423            auth_header=auth_header)

1425    @staticmethod
1426    def _build_save_streaming_file_url(model_class, pk):
1427        return "rest/{model_class}/save-file-streaming/{pk}/".format(
1428            model_class=model_class.lower(), pk=pk)
1429
1430    def save_streaming_file(self, model_class: str, pk: int, file_field: str,
1431                            file: io.BufferedReader, file_name: str = None,
1432                            auth_header: dict = None):
1433        """
1434        Stream file to PumpWood.
1435
1436        Args:
1437            model_class (str): Model class of the object.
1438            pk (int): pk of the object.
1439            file_field (str): File field that will receive file stream.
1440            file (io.BufferedReader): File to upload.
1441
1442        Kwargs:
1443            file_name (str): Name of the file, is not set it will be saved as
1444                {pk}__{file_field}.{extension at permited extension}
1445            auth_header (dict): Authentication dictionary.
1446        """
1447        request_header = self._check__auth_header(auth_header=auth_header)
1448        request_header["Content-Type"] = "application/octet-stream"
1449        post_url = self.server_url + self._build_save_streaming_file_url(
1450            model_class=model_class, pk=pk)
1451
1452        parameters = {}
1453        parameters["file_field"] = file_field
1454        if file_name is not None:
1455            parameters["file_name"] = file_name
1456
1457        response = requests.post(
1458            url=post_url, data=file, params=parameters,
1459            verify=self.verify_ssl, headers=request_header, stream=True)
1460
1461        file_last_bite = file.tell()
1462        self.error_handler(response)
1463        json_response = PumpWoodMicroService.angular_json(response)
1464
1465        if file_last_bite != json_response["bytes_uploaded"]:
1466            template = "Saved bytes in streaming [{}] differ from file " + \
1467                "bites [{}]."
1468            raise PumpWoodException(
1469                    template.format(
1470                        json_response["bytes_uploaded"], file_last_bite))
1471        return json_response["file_path"]

1757    @staticmethod
1758    def _build_pivot_url(model_class):
1759        return "rest/%s/pivot/" % (model_class.lower(), )

1761    def pivot(self, model_class: str, columns: list = [], format: str = 'list',
1762              filter_dict: dict = {}, exclude_dict: dict = {},
1763              order_by: list = [], variables: list = None,
1764              show_deleted=False, auth_header: dict = None):
1765        """
1766        Pivot object data acording to columns specified.
1767
1768        Args:
1769            model_class (str): Model class to be pivoted.
1770        Kwargs:
1771            columns (str): Fields to be used as columns.
1772            format (str): Format to be used to convert pandas.DataFrame to
1773                          dictionary, must be in ['dict','list','series',
1774                          'split', 'records','index'].
1775            filter_dict (dict): Dictionary to to be used in objects.filter
1776                                argument (Same as list end-point).
1777            exclude_dict (dict): Dictionary to to be used in objects.exclude
1778                                 argument (Same as list end-point).
1779            order_by (list): Dictionary to to be used in objects.order_by
1780                             argument (Same as list end-point).
1781            variables (list[str]) = None: List of the variables to be returned,
1782                if None, the default variables will be returned.
1783            show_deleted (bool): If deleted data should be returned.
1784            auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.
1785        Returns:
1786            dict or list: Depends on format type used to convert
1787                          pandas.DataFrame
1788        Raises:
1789            Dependends on backend implementation
1790        Example:
1791            No example yet.
1792        """
1793        url_str = self._build_pivot_url(model_class)
1794        post_data = {
1795            'columns': columns, 'format': format,
1796            'filter_dict': filter_dict, 'exclude_dict': exclude_dict,
1797            'order_by': order_by, "variables": variables,
1798            "show_deleted": show_deleted}
1799        return self.request_post(
1800            url=url_str, data=post_data, auth_header=auth_header)
1801
1802    def _flat_list_by_chunks_helper(self, args):
1803        try:
1804            # Unpacking arguments
1805            model_class = args["model_class"]
1806            filter_dict = args["filter_dict"]
1807            exclude_dict = args["exclude_dict"]
1808            fields = args["fields"]
1809            show_deleted = args["show_deleted"]
1810            auth_header = args["auth_header"]
1811            chunk_size = args["chunk_size"]
1812
1813            temp_filter_dict = copy.deepcopy(filter_dict)
1814            url_str = self._build_pivot_url(model_class)
1815            max_pk = 0
1816
1817            # Fetch data until an empty result is returned
1818            list_dataframes = []
1819            while True:
1820                sys.stdout.write(".")
1821                sys.stdout.flush()
1822                temp_filter_dict["id__gt"] = max_pk
1823                post_data = {
1824                    'format': 'list',
1825                    'filter_dict': temp_filter_dict,
1826                    'exclude_dict': exclude_dict,
1827                    'order_by': ["id"], "variables": fields,
1828                    "show_deleted": show_deleted,
1829                    "limit": chunk_size,
1830                    "add_pk_column": True}
1831                temp_dateframe = pd.DataFrame(self.request_post(
1832                    url=url_str, data=post_data, auth_header=auth_header))
1833
1834                # Break if results are less than chunk size, so no more results
1835                # are avaiable
1836                if len(temp_dateframe) < chunk_size:
1837                    list_dataframes.append(temp_dateframe)
1838                    break
1839
1840                max_pk = int(temp_dateframe["id"].max())
1841                list_dataframes.append(temp_dateframe)
1842
1843            if len(list_dataframes) == 0:
1844                return pd.DataFrame()
1845            else:
1846                return pd.concat(list_dataframes)
1847        except Exception as e:
1848            raise Exception("Exception at flat_list_by_chunks:", str(e))
1849
1850    def flat_list_by_chunks(self, model_class: str, filter_dict: dict = {},
1851                            exclude_dict: dict = {}, fields: list = None,
1852                            show_deleted: bool = False,
1853                            auth_header: dict = None,
1854                            chunk_size: int = 1000000,
1855                            n_parallel: int = None,
1856                            create_composite_pk: bool = False,
1857                            start_date: str = None,
1858                            end_date: str = None):
1859        """
1860        Use the same end-point as pivot which does not unserialize results.
1861
1862        Args:
1863            model_class (str): Model class to be pivoted.
1864
1865        Kwargs:
1866            filter_dict (dict): Dictionary to to be used in objects.filter
1867                                argument (Same as list end-point).
1868            exclude_dict (dict): Dictionary to to be used in objects.exclude
1869                                 argument (Same as list end-point).
1870            fields (list[str]) = None: List of the variables to be returned,
1871                if None, the default variables will be returned.
1872            show_deleted (bool): If deleted data should be returned.
1873            auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.
1874            chunk_size (int): Limit of data to fetch per call.
1875            n_parallel (int): Number of parallel process to perform.
1876
1877        Returns:
1878            dict or list: Depends on format type used to convert
1879                          pandas.DataFrame
1880
1881        Raises:
1882            Dependends on backend implementation
1883
1884        Example:
1885            No example yet.
1886        """
1887        if n_parallel is None:
1888            n_parallel = int(os.getenv(
1889                "PUMPWOOD_COMUNICATION__N_PARALLEL", 4))
1890
1891        temp_filter_dict = copy.deepcopy(filter_dict)
1892        fill_options = self.fill_options(
1893            model_class=model_class, auth_header=auth_header)
1894        primary_keys = fill_options["pk"]["column"]
1895        partition = fill_options["pk"].get("partition", [])
1896
1897        # Create a list of month and include start and end dates if not at
1898        # the beginning of a month
1899        month_sequence = None
1900        if (start_date is not None) and (end_date is not None):
1901            start_date = pd.to_datetime(start_date)
1902            end_date = pd.to_datetime(end_date)
1903            list_month_sequence = pd.date_range(
1904                start=start_date, end=end_date, freq='MS').tolist()
1905            month_sequence = pd.Series(
1906                [start_date] + list_month_sequence + [end_date]
1907            ).sort_values().tolist()
1908
1909            month_df = pd.DataFrame({'end': month_sequence})
1910            month_df['start'] = month_df['end'].shift()
1911            month_df = month_df.dropna().drop_duplicates()
1912            month_sequence = month_df.to_dict("records")
1913        elif (start_date is not None) or (end_date is not None):
1914            msg = (
1915                "To break query in chunks using start_date and end_date "
1916                "both must be set.\n"
1917                "start_date: {start_date}\n"
1918                "end_date: {end_date}\n").format(
1919                    start_date=start_date, end_date=end_date)
1920            raise PumpWoodException(
1921                message=msg, payload={
1922                    "start_date": start_date,
1923                    "end_date": end_date})
1924
1925        resp_df = pd.DataFrame()
1926        ##########################################################
1927        # If table have more than one partition, run in parallel #
1928        # the {partition}__in elements along with dates          #
1929        if 1 < len(partition):
1930            partition_col_1st = partition[0]
1931            filter_dict_keys = list(temp_filter_dict.keys())
1932            partition_filter = None
1933            count_partition_col_1st_filters = 0
1934            for col in filter_dict_keys:
1935                if partition_col_1st + "__in" == col:
1936                    partition_filter = temp_filter_dict[col]
1937                    del temp_filter_dict[col]
1938                    count_partition_col_1st_filters = \
1939                        count_partition_col_1st_filters + 1
1940                elif partition_col_1st == col:
1941                    partition_filter = [temp_filter_dict[col]]
1942                    del temp_filter_dict[col]
1943                    count_partition_col_1st_filters = \
1944                        count_partition_col_1st_filters + 1
1945
1946            # Validating query for partitioned tables
1947            if partition_filter is None:
1948                msg = (
1949                    "Table is partitioned with sub-partitions, running "
1950                    "queries without at least first level partition will "
1951                    "lead to long waiting times or hanging queries. Please "
1952                    "use first partition level in filter_dict with equal "
1953                    "or in operators. Table partitions: {}"
1954                ).format(partition)
1955                raise PumpWoodException(message=msg)
1956
1957            if 1 < count_partition_col_1st_filters:
1958                msg = (
1959                    "Please give some help for the dev here, use just one "
1960                    "filter_dict entry for first partition...")
1961                raise PumpWoodException(message=msg)
1962
1963            # Parallelizing query using partition columns
1964            pool_arguments = []
1965            for filter_key in partition_filter:
1966                request_filter_dict = copy.deepcopy(temp_filter_dict)
1967                request_filter_dict[partition_col_1st] = filter_key
1968                if month_sequence is None:
1969                    pool_arguments.append({
1970                        "model_class": model_class,
1971                        "filter_dict": request_filter_dict,
1972                        "exclude_dict": exclude_dict,
1973                        "fields": fields,
1974                        "show_deleted": show_deleted,
1975                        "auth_header": auth_header,
1976                        "chunk_size": chunk_size})
1977                else:
1978                    for i in range(len(month_sequence)):
1979                        request_filter_dict_t = copy.deepcopy(
1980                            request_filter_dict)
1981                        # If is not the last interval, query using open
1982                        # right interval so subsequence querys does
1983                        # not overlap
1984                        if i != len(month_sequence) - 1:
1985                            request_filter_dict_t["time__gte"] = \
1986                                month_sequence[i]["start"]
1987                            request_filter_dict_t["time__lt"] = \
1988                                month_sequence[i]["end"]
1989
1990                        # At the last interaval use closed right interval so
1991                        # last element is also included in the interval
1992                        else:
1993                            request_filter_dict_t["time__gte"] = \
1994                                month_sequence[i]["start"]
1995                            request_filter_dict_t["time__lte"] = \
1996                                month_sequence[i]["end"]
1997
1998                        pool_arguments.append({
1999                            "model_class": model_class,
2000                            "filter_dict": request_filter_dict_t,
2001                            "exclude_dict": exclude_dict,
2002                            "fields": fields,
2003                            "show_deleted": show_deleted,
2004                            "auth_header": auth_header,
2005                            "chunk_size": chunk_size})
2006
2007            # Perform parallel calls to backend each chucked by chunk_size
2008            print("## Starting parallel flat list: %s" % len(pool_arguments))
2009            try:
2010                with Pool(n_parallel) as p:
2011                    results = p.map(
2012                        self._flat_list_by_chunks_helper,
2013                        pool_arguments)
2014                resp_df = pd.concat(results)
2015            except Exception as e:
2016                PumpWoodException(message=str(e))
2017            print("\n## Finished parallel flat list: %s" % len(pool_arguments))
2018
2019        ############################################
2020        # If table have partition, run in parallel #
2021        else:
2022            try:
2023                results_key_data = self._flat_list_by_chunks_helper({
2024                    "model_class": model_class,
2025                    "filter_dict": temp_filter_dict,
2026                    "exclude_dict": exclude_dict,
2027                    "fields": fields,
2028                    "show_deleted": show_deleted,
2029                    "auth_header": auth_header,
2030                    "chunk_size": chunk_size})
2031                resp_df = results_key_data
2032            except Exception as e:
2033                PumpWoodException(message=str(e))
2034
2035        if (1 < len(partition)) and create_composite_pk:
2036            print("## Creating composite pk")
2037            resp_df["pk"] = resp_df[primary_keys].apply(
2038                CompositePkBase64Converter.dump,
2039                primary_keys=primary_keys, axis=1)
2040        return resp_df
2041
2042    @staticmethod
2043    def _build_bulk_save_url(model_class: str):
2044        return "rest/%s/bulk-save/" % (model_class.lower(),)

2046    def bulk_save(self, model_class: str, data_to_save: list,
2047                  auth_header: dict = None):
2048        """
2049        Save a list of objects.
2050
2051        Args:
2052            model_class(str): Data model class.
2053            data_to_save(list): A list of objects to be saved.
2054        Kwargs:
2055            auth_header(dict): A dictionary with authorization headers.
2056        Return:
2057            dict['saved_count']: Number of saved objects.
2058        """

2060        return self.request_post(url=url_str, data=data_to_save,
2061                                 auth_header=auth_header)

2065    def _request_get_wrapper(self, arguments: dict):
2066        try:
2067            results = self.request_get(**arguments)
2068            sys.stdout.write(".")
2069            sys.stdout.flush()
2070            return results
2071        except Exception as e:
2072            raise Exception("Error on parallel get: " + str(e))

2074    @staticmethod
2075    def flatten_parallel(parallel_result: list):
2076        """
2077        Concat all parallel return to one list.
2078
2079        Args:
2080            parallel_result (list): A list of lists to be flated (concatenate
2081                all lists into one).
2082        Return:
2083            A list with all sub list itens.
2084        """
2085        return [
2086            item for sublist in parallel_result
2087            for item in sublist]

2089    def parallel_request_get(self, urls_list: list, n_parallel: int = None,
2090                             auth_header: dict = None):
2091        """
2092        Make many [n_parallel] get request.
2093
2094        Args:
2095            urls_list (list): List of urls to make get requests.
2096        Kwargs:
2097            n_parallel (int): Number of simultaneus get requests, if not set
2098                get from PUMPWOOD_COMUNICATION__N_PARALLEL env variable, if
2099                not set then 4 will be considered.
2100            auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.
2101        Returns:
2102            list: List of the get request reponses.
2103        Raises:
2104            No particular raises
2105        Example:
2106            No example yet.
2107
2108        """
2109        if n_parallel is None:
2110            n_parallel = int(os.getenv(
2111                "PUMPWOOD_COMUNICATION__N_PARALLEL", 4))
2112
2113        pool_arguments = [
2114            {'url': u, 'auth_header': auth_header} for u in urls_list]
2115
2116        with Pool(n_parallel) as p:
2117            results = p.map(self._request_get_wrapper, pool_arguments)
2118        print("|")
2119        return results

2130    def paralell_request_post(self, urls_list: list, data_list: list,
2131                              n_parallel: int = None,
2132                              auth_header: dict = None):
2133        """
2134        Make many [n_parallel] post request.
2135
2136        Args:
2137            urls_list (list<str>): List of urls to make get requests.
2138            data_list (list<any>): List of data to be used as post payloads.
2139        Kwargs:
2140            n_parallel (int): Number of simultaneus get requests, if not set
2141                get from PUMPWOOD_COMUNICATION__N_PARALLEL env variable, if
2142                not set then 4 will be considered.
2143            auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.
2144        Returns:
2145            list: List of the post request reponses.
2146        Raises:
2147            No particular raises
2148        Example:
2149            No example yet.
2150
2151        """
2152        if len(urls_list) != len(data_list):
2153            raise Exception(
2154                'len(urls_list) must be equal to len(data_list)')
2155
2156        pool_arguments = []
2157        for i in range(len(urls_list)):
2158            pool_arguments.append(
2159                {'url': urls_list[i], 'data': data_list[i],
2160                 'auth_header': auth_header})
2161
2162        with Pool(n_parallel) as p:
2163            results = p.map(self._request_post_wrapper, pool_arguments)
2164        print("|")
2165        return results

2209        """
2210        Make many [n_parallel] retrieve request.
2211
2212        Args:
2213            model_class (str, List[str]): Model Class to retrieve.
2214            list_pk (List[int]): List of the pks to retrieve.
2215        Kwargs:
2216            n_parallel (int): Number of simultaneus get requests, if not set
2217                get from PUMPWOOD_COMUNICATION__N_PARALLEL env variable, if
2218                not set then 4 will be considered.
2219            auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.
2220        Returns:
2221            list: List of the retrieve request reponses.
2222        Raises:
2223            No particular raises
2224        Example:
2225            No example yet.
2226
2227        """
2228        if n_parallel is None:
2229            n_parallel = int(os.getenv(
2230                "PUMPWOOD_COMUNICATION__N_PARALLEL", 4))
2231
2232        if type(model_class) != list:
2233            model_class = [model_class]*len(list_pk)
2234
2235        if len(model_class) != len(list_pk):
2236            raise Exception('len(model_class) != len(list_pk)')
2237
2238        urls_list = [
2239            self._build_retrieve_url(model_class=model_class[i],
2240                                     pk=list_pk[i])
2241            for i in range(len(model_class))]
2242        return self.parallel_request_get(
2243            urls_list=urls_list, n_parallel=n_parallel,
2244            auth_header=auth_header)

2246    def _request_retrieve_file_wrapper(self, args):
2247        sys.stdout.write(".")
2248        sys.stdout.flush()
2249        try:
2250            return self.retrieve_file(**args)
2251        except Exception as e:
2252            raise Exception("Error in parallel retrieve_file: " + str(e))
2253
2254    def parallel_retrieve_file(self, model_class: str,
2255                               list_pk: List[int], file_field: str = None,
2256                               save_path: str = "./", save_file: bool = True,
2257                               list_file_name: List[str] = None,
2258                               if_exists: str = "fail",
2259                               n_parallel: int = None,
2260                               auth_header: dict = None):
2261        """
2262        Make many [n_parallel] retrieve request.
2263
2264        Args:
2265            model_class (str, List[str]): Model Class to retrieve.
2266            list_pk (List[int]): List of the pks to retrieve.
2267            file_field (str): Indicates the file field to download from.
2268        Kwargs:
2269            n_parallel (int): Number of simultaneus get requests, if not set
2270                get from PUMPWOOD_COMUNICATION__N_PARALLEL env variable, if
2271                not set then 4 will be considered.
2272            save_path (str) = "./"
2273            save_file (bool) = True: True save file locally, False return
2274                file content as bites.
2275            list_file_name (List[str]) = None: Set a file name for each file
2276                download.
2277            if_exists (str) = "fail": Set how treat when a file will be saved
2278                and there is another at same path. "fail" will raise an error;
2279                "overwrite" will overwrite the file with the new one; "skip"
2280                when list_file_name is set, check before downloaded it file
2281                already exists, if so skip the download.
2282            auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.
2283
2284        Returns:
2285            list: List of the retrieve request reponses.
2286        Raises:
2287            No particular raises
2288        Example:
2289            No example yet.
2290
2291        """
2292        if n_parallel is None:
2293            n_parallel = int(os.getenv(
2294                "PUMPWOOD_COMUNICATION__N_PARALLEL", 4))
2295
2296        if list_file_name is not None:
2297            if len(list_file_name) != len(list_pk):
2298                raise PumpWoodException((
2299                    "Lenght of list_file_name and list_pk are not equal:\n"
2300                    "len(list_file_name)={list_file_name}; "
2301                    "len(list_pk)={list_pk}").format(
2302                        list_file_name=len(list_file_name),
2303                        list_pk=len(list_pk)))
2304
2305        pool_arguments = []
2306        for i in range(len(list_pk)):
2307            pk = list_pk[i]
2308            file_name = None
2309            if list_file_name is not None:
2310                file_name = list_file_name[i]
2311
2312            pool_arguments.append({
2313                "model_class": model_class, "pk": pk,
2314                "file_field": file_field, "auth_header": auth_header,
2315                "save_file": save_file, "file_name": file_name,
2316                "save_path": save_path, "if_exists": if_exists})
2317
2318        try:
2319            with Pool(n_parallel) as p:
2320                results = p.map(
2321                    self._request_retrieve_file_wrapper,
2322                    pool_arguments)
2323            print("|")
2324        except Exception as e:
2325            raise PumpWoodException(str(e))
2326
2327        return results
2328
2329    def parallel_list(self, model_class: Union[str, List[str]],
2330                      list_args: List[dict], n_parallel: int = None,
2331                      auth_header: dict = None):
2332        """
2333        Make many [n_parallel] list request.
2334
2335        Args:
2336            model_class (str): Model Class to retrieve.
2337            list_args_list (list): A list of list request args (filter_dict,
2338                                   exclude_dict, order_by).
2339        Kwargs:
2340            n_parallel (int): Number of simultaneus get requests, if not set
2341                get from PUMPWOOD_COMUNICATION__N_PARALLEL env variable, if
2342                not set then 4 will be considered.
2343            auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.
2344        Returns:
2345            list: List of the retrieve request reponses.
2346        Raises:
2347            No particular raises
2348        Example:
2349            No example yet.
2350
2351        """
2352        if n_parallel is None:
2353            n_parallel = int(os.getenv(
2354                "PUMPWOOD_COMUNICATION__N_PARALLEL", 4))
2355
2356        urls_list = None
2357        if type(model_class) == str:
2358            urls_list = [self._build_list_url(model_class)]*len(list_args)
2359        else:
2360            if len(model_class) != len(list_args):
2361                raise Exception('len(model_class) != len(list_args)')
2362            urls_list = [self._build_list_url(m) for m in model_class]
2363
2364        print("## Starting parallel_list: %s" % len(urls_list))
2365        return self.paralell_request_post(
2366            urls_list=urls_list, data_list=list_args,
2367            n_parallel=n_parallel, auth_header=auth_header)
