2488    def parallel_delete(self, model_class: Union[str, List[str]],
2489                        list_pk: List[int], n_parallel: int = None,
2490                        auth_header: dict = None):
2491        """
2492        Make many [n_parallel] delete requests.
2493
2494        Args:
2495            model_class (str): Model Class to retrieve.
2496            list_obj_dict (list<dict>): List of dictionaries containing
2497                PumpWood objects (must have at least 'model_class' key)
2498        Kwargs:
2499            n_parallel (int): Number of simultaneus get requests, if not set
2500                get from PUMPWOOD_COMUNICATION__N_PARALLEL env variable, if
2501                not set then 4 will be considered.
2502            auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.
2503        Returns:
2504            list: List of the retrieve request reponses.
2505        Raises:
2506            No particular raises
2507        Example:
2508            No example yet.
2509
2510        """
2511        if n_parallel is None:
2512            n_parallel = int(os.getenv(
2513                "PUMPWOOD_COMUNICATION__N_PARALLEL", 4))
2514
2515        if type(model_class) != list:
2516            model_class = [model_class]*len(list_pk)
2517
2518        if len(model_class) != len(list_pk):
2519            raise Exception('len(model_class) != len(list_pk)')
2520
2521        urls_list = [
2522            self._build_delete_request_url(model_class=model_class[i],
2523                                           pk=list_pk[i])
2524            for i in range(len(model_class))]
2525

2527        return self.parallel_request_get(
2528            urls_list=urls_list, n_parallel=n_parallel,

2575    def parallel_execute_action(self, model_class: Union[str, List[str]],

2578                                parameters: Union[dict, List[dict]] = {},
2579                                n_parallel: int = None,
2580                                auth_header: dict = None):
2581        """
2582        Make many [n_parallel] execute_action requests.
2583
2584        Args:
2585            model_class (str, list(str)): Model Class to perform action over,
2586                or a list of model class o make diferent actions.
2587            pk (int, list[int]): A list of the pks to perform action or a
2588                single pk to perform action with different paraemters.
2589            action (str, list[str]): A list of actions to perform or a single
2590                action to perform over all pks and parameters.
2591        Kwargs:
2592            parameters (dict, list[dict]): Parameters used to perform actions
2593                or a single dict to be used in all actions.
2594            n_parallel (int): Number of simultaneus get requests, if not set
2595                get from PUMPWOOD_COMUNICATION__N_PARALLEL env variable, if
2596                not set then 4 will be considered.
2597            auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.
2598        Returns:
2599            list: List of the retrieve request reponses.
2600        Raises:
2601            No particular raises
2602        Example:
2603            No example yet.
2604
2605        """
2606        if n_parallel is None:
2607            n_parallel = int(os.getenv(
2608                "PUMPWOOD_COMUNICATION__N_PARALLEL", 4))
2609
2610        parallel_length = None
2611        if type(model_class) == list:
2612            if parallel_length is not None:
2613                if parallel_length != len(model_class):
2614                    raise Exception('parallel_length != len(model_class)')
2615            else:
2616                parallel_length = len(model_class)
2617        if type(pk) == list:
2618            if parallel_length is not None:
2619                if parallel_length != len(pk):
2620                    raise Exception('parallel_length != len(pk)')
2621            else:
2622                parallel_length = len(pk)
2623        if type(action) == list:
2624            if parallel_length is not None:
2625                if parallel_length != len(action):
2626                    raise Exception('parallel_length != len(action)')
2627            else:
2628                parallel_length = len(action)
2629        if type(parameters) == list:
2630            if parallel_length is not None:
2631                if parallel_length != len(parameters):
2632                    raise Exception('parallel_length != len(parameters)')
2633            else:
2634                parallel_length = len(parameters)
2635
2636        model_class = model_class if type(model_class) == list \
2637            else [model_class]*parallel_length
2638        pk = pk if type(pk) == list \
2639            else [pk]*parallel_length
2640        action = action if type(action) == list \
2641            else [action]*parallel_length
2642        parameters = parameters if type(parameters) == list \
2643            else [parameters]*parallel_length
2644
2645        urls_list = [
2646            self._build_execute_action_url(
2647                model_class=model_class[i], action=action[i], pk=pk[i])
2648            for i in range(parallel_length)]
2649
2650        print("## Starting parallel_execute_action: %s" % len(urls_list))
2651        return self.paralell_request_post(
2652            urls_list=urls_list, data_list=parameters,
2653            n_parallel=n_parallel, auth_header=auth_header)

def break_in_chunks(df_to_break: pandas.core.frame.DataFrame, chunksize: int = 1000): 
43def break_in_chunks(df_to_break: pd.DataFrame, chunksize: int = 1000):
44    """Break a dataframe in chunks of chunksize."""
45    to_return = list()
46    for g, df in df_to_break.groupby(np.arange(len(df_to_break)) // chunksize):
47        to_return.append(df)
48    return to_return

class PumpWoodMicroService: 
  51class PumpWoodMicroService():
  52    """Class to define an inter-pumpwood MicroService."""

  54    @staticmethod
  55    def _ajust_server_url(server_url):
  56        if server_url is None:
  57            return None
  58        if server_url[-1] != '/':
  59            return server_url + '/'
  60        else:
  61            return server_url
  62
  63    def __init__(self, name: str = None, server_url: str = None,
  64                 username: str = None, password: str = None,
  65                 verify_ssl: bool = True, auth_suffix: str = None,
  66                 debug: bool = None):
  67        """
  68        Create new PumpWoodMicroService object.
  69
  70        Creates a new microservice object. If just name is passed, object must
  71        be initiate after with init() method.
  72
  73        Args:
  74            name (str): Name of the microservice, helps when exceptions
  75                        are raised.
  76        Kwargs:
  77            server_url (str): url of the server that will be connected.
  78            username (str): Username that will be logged on.
  79            password (str): Variable to be converted to JSON and posted along
  80            with the request
  81            verify_ssl (bool): Set if microservice will verify ssl certificate
  82        Returns:
  83            PumpWoodMicroService: New PumpWoodMicroService object
  84        Raises:
  85            No particular Raises
  86        Example:
  87            No example
  88        """
  89        self.name = name
  90        self.__headers = None
  91        self.__user = None
  92        self.__username = username
  93        self.__password = password
  94        self.server_url = self._ajust_server_url(server_url)
  95        self.verify_ssl = verify_ssl
  96        self.__base_header = {'Content-Type': 'application/json'}
  97        self.__auth_header = None
  98        self.__token_expiry = None
  99        self.auth_suffix = auth_suffix
 100        self.debug = debug
 101        self.is_mfa_login = False

 103    def init(self, name: str, server_url: str, username: str,
 104             password: str, verify_ssl: bool = True, auth_suffix: str = None,
 105             debug: bool = None):
 106        """
 107        Start a microservice after creation.
 108
 109        Usefull in flask app config.
 110
 111        Args:
 112            name (str): Name of the microservice, helps when exceptions
 113                        are raised.
 114            server_url (str): url of the server that will be connected.
 115            user_name (str): Username that will be logged on.
 116            password (str): Variable to be converted to JSON and posted along
 117            with the request
 118            verify_ssl (bool): Set if microservice will verify ssl certificate
 119        Kwargs:
 120            auth_suffix (str): Add a suffix to auth end-point in case of
 121                authentication end-point have any suffix.
 122        Returns:
 123            No return
 124        Raises:
 125            No particular Raises
 126        Example:
 127            No example
 128        """
 129        self.name = name
 130        self.__headers = None
 131        self.__username = username
 132        self.__password = password
 133        self.server_url = self._ajust_server_url(server_url)
 134        self.verify_ssl = verify_ssl
 135        self.auth_suffix = auth_suffix
 136        self.debug = debug

 138    @staticmethod
 139    def angular_json(request_result):
 140        """
 141        Convert text to Json removing any XSSI at the beging of JSON.
 142
 143        Args:
 144            request_result (Request): JSON Request to be converted
 145        Kwargs:
 146            No Kwargs
 147        Returns:
 148            No return
 149        Raises:
 150            No particular Raises
 151        Example:
 152            No example
 153        """
 154        if request_result.text == '':
 155            return None
 156
 157        string_start = ")]}',\n"
 158        try:
 159            if request_result.text[:6] == string_start:
 160                return (json.loads(request_result.text[6:]))
 161            else:
 162                return (json.loads(request_result.text))
 163        except Exception:
 164            return {"error": "Can not decode to Json",
 165                    'msg': request_result.text}
 166
 167    def time_to_expiry(self) -> pd.Timedelta:
 168        """
 169        Return time to token expiry.
 170
 171        Args:
 172            No Args.
 173        Kwargs:
 174            No Kwargs.
 175        Return:
 176            Return time until token expiration.
 177        """
 178        if self.__token_expiry is None:
 179            return None
 180
 181        now_datetime = pd.to_datetime(datetime.datetime.utcnow(), utc=True)
 182        time_to_expiry = self.__token_expiry - now_datetime
 183        return time_to_expiry
 184
 185    def is_credential_set(self) -> bool:
 186        """
 187        Check if username and password are set on object.
 188
 189        Args:
 190            No Args.
 191        Kwargs:
 192            No Kwargs.
 193        Return:
 194            True if usename and password were set during object creation or
 195            later with init function.
 196        """
 197        return not (self.__username is None or self.__password is None)
 198
 199    def login(self, force_refresh: bool = False) -> None:
 200        """
 201        Log microservice in using username and password provided.
 202
 203        Args:
 204            No Args.
 205        Kwargs:
 206            force_refresh [bool]: Force token refresh despise still valid
 207                according to self.__token_expiry.
 208        Returns:
 209            No return
 210        Raises:
 211            Exception: If login response has status diferent from 200.
 212        Example:
 213            No example
 214
 215        """
 216        if not self.is_credential_set():
 217            raise PumpWoodUnauthorized(
 218                message="Microservice username or/and password not set")
 219
 220        # Check if expiry time is 1h from now
 221        refresh_expiry = False
 222        if self.__token_expiry is None:
 223            refresh_expiry = True
 224        else:
 225            time_to_expiry = self.time_to_expiry()
 226            if time_to_expiry < datetime.timedelta(hours=1):
 227                refresh_expiry = True
 228
 229        # When if debug always refresh token
 230        is_debug = None
 231        if self.debug is None:
 232            is_debug = os.getenv("DEBUG", "FALSE") == "TRUE"
 233        else:
 234            is_debug = self.debug
 235
 236        if refresh_expiry or force_refresh or is_debug:
 237            login_url = None
 238            if self.auth_suffix is None:
 239                login_url = urljoin(
 240                    self.server_url, 'rest/registration/login/')
 241            else:
 242                temp_url = 'rest/{suffix}registration/login/'.format(
 243                    suffix=self.auth_suffix.lower())
 244                login_url = urljoin(self.server_url, temp_url)
 245
 246            login_result = requests.post(
 247                login_url, json={
 248                    'username': self.__username,
 249                    'password': self.__password},
 250                verify=self.verify_ssl)
 251
 252            login_data = {}
 253            try:
 254                login_data = PumpWoodMicroService.angular_json(login_result)
 255                login_result.raise_for_status()
 256            except Exception as e:
 257                raise PumpWoodUnauthorized(
 258                    message="Login not possible.\nError: " + str(e),
 259                    payload=login_data)
 260
 261            if 'mfa_token' in login_data.keys():
 262                login_data = self.confirm_mfa_code(mfa_login_data=login_data)
 263
 264            self.__auth_header = {
 265                'Authorization': 'Token ' + login_data['token']}
 266            self.__user = login_data["user"]
 267            self.__token_expiry = pd.to_datetime(login_data['expiry'])
 268
 269    def confirm_mfa_code(self, mfa_login_data: dict) -> dict:
 270        """
 271        Ask user to confirm MFA code to login.
 272
 273        Args:
 274            mfa_login_data [dict]: Result from login request with 'mfa_token'
 275                as key.
 276        Return [dict]:
 277            Return login returned with MFA confimation.
 278        Raise:
 279            Raise error if reponse is not valid.
 280        """
 281        code = input("## Please enter MFA code: ")
 282        url = urljoin(
 283            self.server_url, 'rest/registration/mfa-validate-code/')
 284        mfa_response = requests.post(url, headers={
 285            "X-PUMPWOOD-MFA-Autorization": mfa_login_data['mfa_token']},
 286            json={"mfa_code": code})
 287        self.error_handler(mfa_response)
 288
 289        # Set is_mfa_login true to indicate that login required MFA
 290        self.is_mfa_login = True
 291        return PumpWoodMicroService.angular_json(mfa_response)
 292

 386    def _check__auth_header(self, auth_header, multipart: bool = False):
 387        """
 388        Check if auth_header is set or auth_header if provided.
 389
 390        Args:
 391            auth_header (dict): AuthHeader to substitute the
 392                                microservice original
 393        Kwargs:
 394            No Kwargs
 395        Returns:
 396            dict: Return a header dict to be used in requests.
 397        Raises:
 398            PumpWoodUnauthorized: If microservice is not logged and a
 399                                  auth_header method argument is not provided.
 400            PumpWoodUnauthorized: If microservice is logged and a auth_header
 401                                  method argument is provided.
 402        Example:
 403            No example
 404
 405        """
 406        if auth_header is None:
 407            # Login will refresh token if it is 1h to expire, it will also
 408            # check if credentials are set.
 409            self.login()
 410            temp__auth_header = self.__auth_header.copy()
 411            if multipart:
 412                return temp__auth_header
 413            else:
 414                temp__auth_header.update(self.__base_header)
 415                return temp__auth_header
 416        else:
 417            if self.is_credential_set():
 418                msg_tmp = (
 419                    'MicroService {name} already looged and '
 420                    'auth_header was provided')
 421                raise PumpWoodUnauthorized(
 422                    msg_tmp.format(name=self.name))
 423
 424            # Set base header as JSON since unserialization is done using
 425            # Pumpwood Communication serialization funciton
 426            temp__auth_header = auth_header.copy()
 427            if multipart:
 428                return temp__auth_header
 429            else:
 430                temp__auth_header.update(self.__base_header)
 431                return temp__auth_header
 432
 433    def error_handler(cls, response):
 434        """
 435        Handle request error.
 436
 437        Check if is a Json and propagate the error with
 438        same type if possible. If not Json raises the content.
 439
 440        Arg:
 441            response (Response): response to be handled.
 442        Kwargs:
 443            No kwargs.
 444        Returns:
 445            No return.
 446        Raises:
 447            Exception: If content-type is not application/json.
 448            Exception: If content-type is application/json, but type not
 449                       present or not recognisable.
 450            Other Exception: If content-type is application/json if type is
 451                             present and recognisable.
 452        Example:
 453            No example
 454
 455        """
 456        if not response.ok:
 457            utcnow = datetime.datetime.utcnow()
 458            response_content_type = response.headers['content-type']
 459
 460            # Request information
 461            url = response.url
 462            method = response.request.method
 463            if 'application/json' not in response_content_type.lower():
 464                # Raise the exception as first in exception deep.
 465                exception_dict = [{
 466                    "exception_url": url,
 467                    "exception_method": method,
 468                    "exception_utcnow": utcnow.isoformat(),
 469                    "exception_deep": 1}]
 470                raise PumpWoodOtherException(
 471                    message=response.text, payload={
 472                        "!exception_stack!": exception_dict})
 473
 474            # Build error stack
 475            response_dict = PumpWoodMicroService.angular_json(response)
 476
 477            # Removing previus error stack
 478            payload = deepcopy(response_dict.get("payload", {}))
 479            exception_stack = deepcopy(payload.pop("!exception_stack!", []))
 480
 481            exception_deep = len(exception_stack)
 482            exception_dict = {
 483                "exception_url": url,
 484                "exception_method": method,
 485                "exception_utcnow": utcnow.isoformat(),
 486                "exception_deep": exception_deep + 1
 487            }
 488            exception_stack.insert(0, exception_dict)
 489            payload["!exception_stack!"] = exception_stack
 490
 491            # Propagate error
 492            exception_message = response_dict.get("message", "")
 493            exception_type = response_dict.get("type", None)
 494            if exception_type is not None:
 495                raise exceptions_dict[exception_type](
 496                    message=exception_message,
 497                    status_code=response.status_code,
 498                    payload=payload)
 499            else:
 500                is_invalid_token = cls.is_invalid_token_response(response)
 501                response_dict["!exception_stack!"] = exception_stack
 502                if is_invalid_token:
 503                    raise PumpWoodUnauthorized(
 504                        message="Invalid token.",
 505                        payload=response.json())
 506                else:
 507                    raise PumpWoodOtherException(
 508                        message="Not mapped exception JSON",
 509                        payload=response_dict)
 510
 511    @classmethod
 512    def is_invalid_token_response(cls,
 513                                  response: requests.models.Response) -> bool:
 514        """
 515        Check if reponse has invalid token error.
 516
 517        Args:
 518            response [requests.models.Response]: Request reponse to check for
 519                invalid token.
 520        Return [bool]:
 521            Return True if response has an invalid token status.
 522        """
 523        if response.status_code == 401:
 524            return True
 525        return False
 526
 527    def request_post(self, url: str, data: any, files: list = None,
 528                     auth_header: dict = None, parameters: dict = {}):
 529        """
 530        Make a POST a request to url with data as Json payload.
 531
 532        Args:
 533            url (str): Url to make the request.
 534            data (any); Data to be used as Json payload.
 535        Kwargs:
 536            files(list of tuples): A list of tuples with
 537                                   (file name, [file1, file2, ...]).
 538            params [dict]: Url parameters.
 539            auth_header(dict): Auth data to overhide microservice's.
 540        Returns:
 541            any: Return the post result
 542        Raises:
 543            Response is passed to error_handler function.
 544        Example:
 545            No example
 546
 547        """
 548        # If parameters are not none convert them to json before
 549        # sending information on query string, 'True' is 'true' on javascript
 550        # for exemple
 551        if parameters is not None:
 552            parameters = copy.deepcopy(parameters)
 553            for key in parameters.keys():
 554                # Do not convert str to json, it put extra "" araound string
 555                if type(parameters[key]) is not str:
 556                    parameters[key] = pumpJsonDump(parameters[key])
 557
 558        response = None
 559        if files is None:
 560            request_header = self._check__auth_header(auth_header=auth_header)
 561            post_url = urljoin(self.server_url, url)
 562            response = requests.post(
 563                url=post_url, data=pumpJsonDump(data),
 564                params=parameters, verify=self.verify_ssl,
 565                headers=request_header)
 566
 567            # Retry request if token is not valid forcing token renew
 568            retry_with_login = (
 569                self.is_invalid_token_response(response) and
 570                auth_header is None)
 571            if retry_with_login:
 572                self.login(force_refresh=True)
 573                request_header = self._check__auth_header(
 574                    auth_header=auth_header)
 575                response = requests.post(
 576                    url=post_url, data=pumpJsonDump(data),
 577                    params=parameters, verify=self.verify_ssl,
 578                    headers=request_header)
 579
 580        # Request with files are done using multipart serializing all fields
 581        # as json
 582        else:
 583            request_header = self._check__auth_header(
 584                auth_header=auth_header, multipart=True)
 585            post_url = urljoin(self.server_url, url)
 586            temp_data = {'__json__': pumpJsonDump(data)}
 587            response = requests.post(
 588                url=post_url, data=temp_data, files=files, params=parameters,
 589                verify=self.verify_ssl, headers=request_header)
 590
 591            retry_with_login = (
 592                self.is_invalid_token_response(response) and
 593                auth_header is None)
 594            if retry_with_login:
 595                self.login(force_refresh=True)
 596                request_header = self._check__auth_header(
 597                    auth_header=auth_header)
 598                response = requests.post(
 599                    url=post_url, data=temp_data, files=files,
 600                    params=parameters, verify=self.verify_ssl,
 601                    headers=request_header)
 602
 603        # Handle errors and re-raise if Pumpwood Exceptions
 604        self.error_handler(response)
 605
 606        # Check if reponse is a file
 607        headers = response.headers
 608        content_disposition = headers.get('content-disposition')
 609        if content_disposition is not None:
 610            file_name = re.findall('filename=(.+)', content_disposition)
 611            if len(file_name) == 1:
 612                return {
 613                    "__file_name__": file_name[0],
 614                    "__content__": response.content}
 615            else:
 616                return {
 617                    "__file_name__": None,
 618                    "__content__": response.content}
 619        else:
 620            return PumpWoodMicroService.angular_json(response)
 621
 622    def request_get(self, url, parameters: dict = {},
 623                    auth_header: dict = None):
 624        """
 625        Make a GET a request to url with data as Json payload.
 626
 627        Args:
 628            url (str): Url to make the request.
 629        Kwargs:
 630            parameters (dict): Url parameters to make the request.
 631            auth_header (dict): Authentication dictionary.
 632        Returns:
 633            any: Return the post result
 634        Raises:
 635            Response is passed to error_handler function.
 636        Example:
 637            No example
 638        """
 639        request_header = self._check__auth_header(auth_header)
 640
 641        # If parameters are not none convert them to json before
 642        # sending information on query string, 'True' is 'true' on javascript
 643        # for example
 644        if parameters is not None:
 645            parameters = copy.deepcopy(parameters)
 646            for key in parameters.keys():
 647                # Do not convert str to json, it put extra "" araound string
 648                if type(parameters[key]) is not str:
 649                    parameters[key] = pumpJsonDump(parameters[key])
 650
 651        get_url = urljoin(self.server_url, url)
 652        response = requests.get(
 653            get_url, verify=self.verify_ssl, headers=request_header,
 654            params=parameters)
 655
 656        retry_with_login = (
 657            self.is_invalid_token_response(response) and
 658            auth_header is None)
 659        if retry_with_login:
 660            self.login(force_refresh=True)
 661            request_header = self._check__auth_header(auth_header=auth_header)
 662            response = requests.get(
 663                get_url, verify=self.verify_ssl, headers=request_header,
 664                params=parameters)
 665
 666        # Re-raise Pumpwood exceptions
 667        self.error_handler(response=response)
 668
 669        json_types = ["application/json", "application/json; charset=utf-8"]
 670        if response.headers['content-type'] in json_types:
 671            return PumpWoodMicroService.angular_json(response)
 672        else:
 673            d = response.headers['content-disposition']
 674            fname = re.findall("filename=(.+)", d)[0]
 675
 676            return {
 677                "content": response.content,
 678                "content-type": response.headers['content-type'],
 679                "filename": fname}
 680
 681    def request_delete(self, url, parameters: dict = None,
 682                       auth_header: dict = None):
 683        """
 684        Make a DELETE a request to url with data as Json payload.
 685
 686        Args:
 687            url (str): Url to make the request.
 688        Kwargs:
 689            parameters (dict): Dictionary with Urls parameters.
 690            auth_header (dict): Auth header if microservice not logged.
 691        Returns:
 692            any: Return the post result
 693        Raises:
 694            Response is passed to error_handler function.
 695        Example:
 696            No example
 697        """
 698        request_header = self._check__auth_header(auth_header)
 699
 700        post_url = self.server_url + url
 701        response = requests.delete(
 702            post_url, verify=self.verify_ssl, headers=request_header,
 703            params=parameters)
 704
 705        # Retry request if token is not valid forcing token renew
 706        retry_with_login = (
 707            self.is_invalid_token_response(response) and
 708            auth_header is None)
 709        if retry_with_login:
 710            self.login(force_refresh=True)
 711            request_header = self._check__auth_header(auth_header=auth_header)
 712            response = requests.delete(
 713                post_url, verify=self.verify_ssl, headers=request_header,
 714                params=parameters)
 715
 716        # Re-raise Pumpwood Exceptions
 717        self.error_handler(response)
 718        return PumpWoodMicroService.angular_json(response)

 720    def list_registered_routes(self, auth_header: dict = None):
 721        """List routes that have been registed at Kong."""
 722        list_url = None
 723        if self.auth_suffix is None:
 724            list_url = 'rest/pumpwood/routes/'
 725        else:
 726            list_url = 'rest/{suffix}pumpwood/routes/'.format(
 727                suffix=self.auth_suffix.lower())
 728        routes = self.request_get(
 729            url=list_url, auth_header=auth_header)
 730        for key, item in routes.items():
 731            item.sort()
 732        return routes
 733
 734    def is_microservice_registered(self, microservice: str,
 735                                   auth_header: dict = None) -> bool:
 736        """
 737        List routes that have been registed at Kong.
 738
 739        Args:
 740            microservice [str]: Service associated with microservice
 741                registered on Pumpwood Kong.
 742        Kwargs:
 743            No Kwargs.
 744        Return:
 745            Return true if microservice is registered.
 746        """
 747        routes = self.list_registered_routes(auth_header=auth_header)
 748        return microservice in routes.keys()

 750    def list_registered_endpoints(self, auth_header: dict = None):
 751        """List routes that have been registed at Kong."""
 752        list_url = None
 753        if self.auth_suffix is None:
 754            list_url = 'rest/pumpwood/endpoints/'
 755        else:
 756            list_url = 'rest/{suffix}pumpwood/endpoints/'.format(
 757                suffix=self.auth_suffix.lower())

 762    def dummy_call(self, payload: dict = None,
 763                   auth_header: dict = None) -> dict:
 764        """
 765        Return a dummy call to ensure headers and payload reaching app.
 766
 767        Args:
 768            No args.
 769        Kwards:
 770            payload (dict]): Payload to be returned by the dummy call
 771                end-point.
 772            auth_header (dict): Auth header if microservice not logged.
 773
 774        Return:
 775            Return a dictonary with:
 776            - full_path (dict): Full path of the request.
 777            - method (dict): Method used at the call
 778            - headers (dict): Headers at the request.
 779            - data (dict): Post payload sent at the request.
 780        """
 781        list_url = None
 782        if self.auth_suffix is None:
 783            list_url = 'rest/pumpwood/dummy-call/'
 784        else:
 785            list_url = 'rest/{suffix}pumpwood/dummy-call/'.format(
 786                suffix=self.auth_suffix.lower())
 787
 788        if payload is None:
 789            return self.request_get(
 790                url=list_url, auth_header=auth_header)
 791        else:
 792            return self.request_post(
 793                url=list_url, data=payload,
 794                auth_header=auth_header)
 795
 796    def dummy_raise(self, exception_class: str, exception_deep: int,
 797                    payload: dict = {}, auth_header: dict = None) -> None:
 798        """
 799        Raise an Pumpwood error with the payload.
 800
 801        Can be used for debug purposes.
 802
 803        Args:
 804            exception_class (str): Class of the exception to be raised.
 805            exception_deep (int): Deep of the exception in microservice
 806                calls.
 807        Kwards:
 808            payload (dict]): Payload to be returned by the dummy call
 809                end-point.
 810            auth_header (dict): Auth header if microservice not logged.
 811        Return:
 812            Should not return any results, all possible call should result
 813            in raising the correspondent error.
 814        Exceptions:
 815            Should raise the correspondent error passed on exception_class
 816            arg, with payload.
 817        """
 818        url = 'rest/pumpwood/dummy-raise/'
 819        payload["exception_class"] = exception_class
 820        payload["exception_deep"] = exception_deep
 821        self.request_post(url=url, data=payload, auth_header=auth_header)
 822
 823    def get_pks_from_unique_field(self, model_class: str, field: str,
 824                                  values: List[Any]) -> pd.DataFrame:
 825        """
 826        Get pk using unique fields values.
 827
 828        Use unique field values to retrieve pk of the objects.
 829
 830        Args:
 831            model_class [str]: Model class of the objects.
 832            field [str]: Unique field to fetch pk.
 833            values [List[Any]]: List of the unique fields used to fetch
 834                primary keys.
 835        Return [pd.DataFrame]:
 836            Return a dataframe in same order as values with columns:
 837                - pk: correspondent primary key of the unique value.
 838                - [field]: Column with same name of field argument,
 839                    correspondent to pk.
 840        """
 841        is_dimension_tag = 'dimensions->' in field
 842        if not is_dimension_tag:
 843            fill_options = self.fill_options(model_class=model_class)
 844            field_details = fill_options.get(field)
 845            if field_details is None:
 846                msg = (
 847                    "Field is not a dimension tag and not found on model "
 848                    "fields. Field [{field}]")
 849                raise PumpWoodQueryException(
 850                    message=msg, payload={"field": field})
 851
 852            is_unique_field = field_details.get("unique", False)
 853            if not is_unique_field:
 854                msg = "Field [{}] to get pk from is not unique"
 855                raise PumpWoodQueryException(
 856                    message=msg, payload={"field": field})
 857
 858        filter_dict = {field + "__in": list(set(values))}
 859        pk_map = None
 860        if not is_dimension_tag:
 861            list_results = pd.DataFrame(self.list_without_pag(
 862                model_class=model_class, filter_dict=filter_dict,
 863                fields=["pk", field]), columns=["pk", field])
 864            pk_map = list_results.set_index(field)["pk"]
 865
 866        # If is dimension tag, fetch dimension and unpack it
 867        else:
 868            dimension_tag = field.split("->")[1]
 869            list_results = pd.DataFrame(self.list_without_pag(
 870                model_class=model_class, filter_dict=filter_dict,
 871                fields=["pk", "dimensions"]))
 872            pk_map = {}
 873            if len(list_results) != 0:
 874                pk_map = list_results\
 875                    .pipe(unpack_dict_columns, columns=["dimensions"])\
 876                    .set_index(dimension_tag)["pk"]
 877
 878        values_series = pd.Series(values)
 879        return pd.DataFrame({
 880            "pk": values_series.map(pk_map).values,
 881            field: values_series
 882        })
 883
 884    @staticmethod
 885    def _build_list_url(model_class: str):
 886        return "rest/%s/list/" % (model_class.lower(),)
 887
 888    def list(self, model_class: str, filter_dict: dict = {},
 889             exclude_dict: dict = {}, order_by: list = [],
 890             auth_header: dict = None, fields: list = None,
 891             default_fields: bool = False, limit: int = None,
 892             foreign_key_fields: bool = False,
 893             **kwargs) -> list:
 894        """
 895        List objects with pagination.
 896
 897        Function to post at list end-point (resumed data) of PumpWood like
 898        systems, results will be paginated. To get next pag, send recived pk at
 899        exclude dict (ex.: exclude_dict={id__in: [1,2,...,30]}).
 900
 901        Args:
 902          model_class (str): Model class of the end-point
 903          filter_dict (dict): Filter dict to be used at the query
 904            (objects.filter arguments).
 905          exclude_dict (dict):  Exclude dict to be used at the query
 906            (objects.exclude arguments).
 907          order_by (list): Ordering list to be used at the query
 908            (objects.order_by arguments).
 909          auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.
 910          fields(list[str]): Select the fields to be returned by the list
 911            end-point.
 912          default_fields [bool]: Return the fields specified at
 913              self.list_fields.
 914          limit [int]: Set the limit of elements of the returned query.
 915          foreign_key_fields [bool]: Return forenging key objects.
 916
 917        Returns:
 918          list: Contaiing objects serialized by list Serializer.
 919
 920        Raises:
 921          No especific raises.
 922
 923        Example:
 924          No example yet.
 925
 926        """
 927        url_str = self._build_list_url(model_class)
 928        post_data = {
 929            'filter_dict': filter_dict, 'exclude_dict': exclude_dict,
 930            'order_by': order_by, 'default_fields': default_fields,
 931            'limit': limit, 'foreign_key_fields': foreign_key_fields}
 932        if fields is not None:
 933            post_data["fields"] = fields
 934        return self.request_post(
 935            url=url_str, data=post_data, auth_header=auth_header)
 936
 937    def list_by_chunks(self, model_class: str, filter_dict: dict = {},
 938                       exclude_dict: dict = {}, auth_header: dict = None,
 939                       fields: list = None, default_fields: bool = False,
 940                       chunk_size: int = 50000, **kwargs) -> list:
 941        """
 942        List object fetching them by chucks using pk to paginate.
 943
 944        List data by chunck to load by datasets without breaking the backend
 945        or receive server timeout. It load chunks orderring the results using
 946        id of the tables, it can be changed but it should be unique otherwise
 947        unexpected results may occur.
 948
 949        Args:
 950          model_class (str): Model class of the end-point
 951
 952        Kwargs:
 953          filter_dict (dict) = {}: Filter dict to be used at the query
 954            (objects.filter arguments).
 955          exclude_dict (dict) = {}:  Exclude dict to be used at the query
 956            (objects.exclude arguments).
 957          auth_header (dict) = None: Dictionary containing the auth header.
 958          fields (list[str]) = None: Select the fields to be returned by the
 959            list end-point.
 960          default_fields (bool) = False: Return the fields specified at
 961              self.list_fields.
 962          chuck_size [int]: Number of objects to be fetched each query.
 963
 964        Returns:
 965          list: Contaiing objects serialized by list Serializer.
 966
 967        Raises:
 968          No especific raises.
 969
 970        Example:
 971          No example yet.
 972
 973        """
 974        copy_filter_dict = copy.deepcopy(filter_dict)
 975
 976        list_all_results = []
 977        max_order_col = 0
 978        while True:
 979            print("- fetching chunk [{}]".format(max_order_col))
 980            copy_filter_dict["pk__gt"] = max_order_col
 981            temp_results = self.list(
 982                model_class=model_class, filter_dict=copy_filter_dict,
 983                exclude_dict=exclude_dict, order_by=["pk"],
 984                auth_header=auth_header, fields=fields,
 985                default_fields=default_fields, limit=chunk_size)
 986
 987            # Break if results is empty
 988            if len(temp_results) == 0:
 989                break
 990
 991            max_order_col = temp_results[-1]["pk"]
 992            list_all_results.extend(temp_results)
 993
 994        return list_all_results
 995
 996    @staticmethod
 997    def _build_list_without_pag_url(model_class: str):
 998        return "rest/%s/list-without-pag/" % (model_class.lower(),)
 999
1000    def list_without_pag(self, model_class: str, filter_dict: dict = {},
1001                         exclude_dict: dict = {}, order_by: list = [],
1002                         auth_header: dict = None, return_type: str = 'list',
1003                         convert_geometry: bool = True, fields: list = None,
1004                         default_fields: bool = False,
1005                         foreign_key_fields: bool = False, **kwargs):
1006        """
1007        List object without pagination.
1008
1009        Function to post at list end-point (resumed data) of PumpWood like
1010        systems, results won't be paginated.
1011        **Be carefull with large returns.**
1012
1013        Args:
1014          model_class (str): Model class of the end-point
1015
1016        Kwargs:
1017          filter_dict (dict): Filter dict to be used at the query
1018            (objects.filter arguments)
1019          exclude_dict (dict):  Exclude dict to be used at the query
1020            (objects.exclude arguments)
1021          order_by (list): Ordering list to be used at the query
1022            (objects.order_by arguments)
1023          auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.
1024          return_type(str): Set the return type, can be [list, dataframe].
1025          convert_geometry(bool) = True: Covert geometry to shapely.
1026          fields(list[str]): Select the fields to be returned by the list
1027            end-point.
1028          default_fields [bool]: Return the fields specified at
1029              self.list_fields.
1030          foreign_key_fields [bool]: Return forenging key objects.
1031        Returns:
1032          list: Contaiing objects serialized by list Serializer.
1033
1034        Raises:
1035          No especific raises.
1036
1037        Example:
1038          No example yet.
1039
1040        """
1041        url_str = self._build_list_without_pag_url(model_class)
1042        post_data = {
1043            'filter_dict': filter_dict, 'exclude_dict': exclude_dict,
1044            'order_by': order_by, 'default_fields': default_fields,
1045            'foreign_key_fields': foreign_key_fields}
1046
1047        if fields is not None:
1048            post_data["fields"] = fields
1049        results = self.request_post(
1050            url=url_str, data=post_data, auth_header=auth_header)
1051
1052        ##################################################
1053        # Converting geometry to Shapely objects in Python
1054        geometry_in_results = False
1055        if convert_geometry:
1056            for obj in results:
1057                geometry_value = obj.get("geometry")
1058                if geometry_value is not None:
1059                    obj["geometry"] = geometry.shape(geometry_value)
1060                    geometry_in_results = True
1061        ##################################################
1062
1063        if return_type == 'list':
1064            return results
1065        elif return_type == 'dataframe':
1066            if (model_class.lower() == "descriptiongeoarea") and \
1067                    geometry_in_results:
1068                return geopd.GeoDataFrame(results, geometry='geometry')
1069            else:
1070                return pd.DataFrame(results)
1071        else:
1072            raise Exception("return_type must be 'list' or 'dataframe'")
1073

1110    def list_dimension_values(self, model_class: str, key: str,
1111                              filter_dict: dict = {}, exclude_dict: dict = {},
1112                              auth_header: dict = None):
1113        """List dimensions avaiable for model_class with the filters.
1114
1115        Parameters
1116        ----------
1117        Args:
1118          model_class: str
1119            Model class of the end-point.
1120          key: str
1121            Key to list the avaiable values using the query filter and exclude.
1122        Kwargs:
1123          filter_dict: dict = {}
1124            Filter dict to be used at the query (objects.filter arguments).
1125          exclude_dict: dict = {}
1126            Exclude dict to be used at the query (objects.exclude arguments).
1127          auth_header: dict= {}
1128            Dictionary containing the auth header.
1129
1130        Returns
1131        -------
1132        list
1133            List of keys avaiable in results from the query dict.
1134        """
1135        url_str = self._build_list_dimension_values(model_class)
1136        post_data = {'filter_dict': filter_dict, 'exclude_dict': exclude_dict,
1137                     'key': key}
1138        return self.request_post(
1139            url=url_str, data=post_data, auth_header=auth_header)

1213    @staticmethod
1214    def _build_retrieve_file_url(model_class: str, pk: int):
1215        return "rest/%s/retrieve-file/%s/" % (model_class.lower(), pk)
1216
1217    def retrieve_file(self, model_class: str, pk: int, file_field: str,
1218                      auth_header: dict = None, save_file: bool = True,
1219                      save_path: str = "./", file_name: str = None,
1220                      if_exists: str = "fail"):
1221        """
1222        Retrieve a file from PumpWood.
1223
1224        Args:
1225          model_class (str): Class of the model to retrieve file.
1226          pk (int): Pk of the object associeted file.
1227          file_field (str): Field of the file to be downloaded.
1228        Kwargs:
1229          auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.
1230          save_file (bool): If data is to be saved as file or return get
1231            response.
1232          save_path (str): Path of the directory to save file.
1233          file_name (str): Name of the file, if None it will have same name as
1234                saved in PumpWood.
1235          if_exists {'fail', 'change_name', 'overwrite', 'skip'}: Set what to
1236            do if there is a file with same name. Skip will not download file
1237            if there is already with same os.path.join(save_path, file_name),
1238            file_name must be set for skip argument.
1239        Returns:
1240          requset.response or str
1241        Raises:
1242          No especific raises.
1243        Example:
1244          No example yet.
1245
1246        """
1247        if if_exists not in ["fail", "change_name", "overwrite", "skip"]:
1248            raise PumpWoodException(
1249                "if_exists must be in ['fail', 'change_name', 'overwrite', "
1250                "'skip']")
1251
1252        if file_name is not None and if_exists == 'skip':
1253            file_path = os.path.join(save_path, file_name)
1254            is_file_already = os.path.isfile(file_path)
1255            if is_file_already:
1256                print("skiping file already exists: ", file_path)
1257                return file_path
1258
1259        url_str = self._build_retrieve_file_url(model_class=model_class, pk=pk)
1260        file_response = self.request_get(
1261            url=url_str, parameters={"file-field": file_field},
1262            auth_header=auth_header)
1263        if not save_file:
1264            return file_response
1265
1266        if not os.path.exists(save_path):
1267            raise PumpWoodException(
1268                "Path to save retrieved file [{}] does not exist".format(
1269                    save_path))
1270
1271        file_name = secure_filename(file_name or file_response["filename"])
1272        file_path = os.path.join(save_path, file_name)
1273        is_file_already = os.path.isfile(file_path)
1274        if is_file_already:
1275            if if_exists == "change_name":
1276                filename, file_extension = os.path.splitext(file_path)
1277                too_many_tries = True
1278                for i in range(10):
1279                    new_path = "{filename}__{count}{extension}".format(
1280                        filename=filename, count=i,
1281                        extension=file_extension)
1282                    if not os.path.isfile(new_path):
1283                        file_path = new_path
1284                        too_many_tries = False
1285                        break
1286                if too_many_tries:
1287                    raise PumpWoodException(
1288                        ("Too many tries to find a not used file name." +
1289                         " file_path[{}]".format(file_path)))
1290
1291            elif if_exists == "fail":
1292                raise PumpWoodException(
1293                    ("if_exists set as 'fail' and there is a file with same" +
1294                     "name. file_path [{}]").format(file_path))
1295
1296        with open(file_path, "wb") as file:
1297            file.write(file_response["content"])
1298        return file_path
1299
1300    @staticmethod
1301    def _build_retrieve_file_straming_url(model_class: str, pk: int):
1302        return "rest/%s/retrieve-file-streaming/%s/" % (
1303            model_class.lower(), pk)
1304
1305    def retrieve_streaming_file(self, model_class: str, pk: int,
1306                                file_field: str, file_name: str,
1307                                auth_header: dict = None,
1308                                save_path: str = "./",
1309                                if_exists: str = "fail"):
1310        """
1311        Retrieve a file from PumpWood.
1312
1313        Args:
1314          model_class (str): Class of the model to retrieve file.
1315          pk (int): Pk of the object associeted file.
1316          file_field (str): Field of the file to be downloaded.
1317          file_name (str): Name of the file, if None it will have same name as
1318                saved in PumpWood.
1319
1320        Kwargs:
1321          auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.
1322          save_path (str): Path of the directory to save file.
1323          if_exists {'fail', 'change_name', 'overwrite'}: Set what to do if
1324            there is a file with same name.
1325
1326        Returns:
1327          requset.response or str
1328
1329        Raises:
1330          No especific raises.
1331
1332        Example:
1333          No example yet.
1334        """
1335        request_header = self._check__auth_header(auth_header)
1336
1337        # begin Args check
1338        if if_exists not in ["fail", "change_name", "overwrite"]:
1339            raise PumpWoodException(
1340                "if_exists must be in ['fail', 'change_name', 'overwrite']")
1341
1342        if not os.path.exists(save_path):
1343            raise PumpWoodException(
1344                "Path to save retrieved file [{}] does not exist".format(
1345                    save_path))
1346        # end Args check
1347
1348        file_path = os.path.join(save_path, file_name)
1349        if os.path.isfile(file_path) and if_exists == "change_name":
1350            filename, file_extension = os.path.splitext(file_path)
1351            too_many_tries = False
1352            for i in range(10):
1353                new_path = "{filename}__{count}{extension}".format(
1354                    filename=filename, count=i,
1355                    extension=file_extension)
1356                if not os.path.isfile(new_path):
1357                    file_path = new_path
1358                    too_many_tries = True
1359                    break
1360            if not too_many_tries:
1361                raise PumpWoodException(
1362                    ("Too many tries to find a not used file name." +
1363                     " file_path[{}]".format(file_path)))
1364
1365        if os.path.isfile(file_path) and if_exists == "fail":
1366            raise PumpWoodException(
1367                ("if_exists set as 'fail' and there is a file with same" +
1368                 "name. file_path [{}]").format(file_path))
1369
1370        url_str = self._build_retrieve_file_straming_url(
1371            model_class=model_class, pk=pk)
1372
1373        get_url = self.server_url + url_str
1374        with requests.get(
1375                get_url, verify=self.verify_ssl, headers=request_header,
1376                params={"file-field": file_field}) as response:
1377            self.error_handler(response)
1378            with open(file_path, 'wb') as f:
1379                for chunk in response.iter_content(chunk_size=8192):
1380                    if chunk:
1381                        f.write(chunk)
1382        return file_path
1383
1384    @staticmethod
1385    def _build_save_url(model_class):
1386        return "rest/%s/save/" % (model_class.lower())
1387
1388    def save(self, obj_dict, files: dict = None, auth_header: dict = None):
1389        """
1390        Save or Update a new object.
1391
1392        Function to save or update a new model_class object. If obj_dict{'pk'}
1393        is None or not defined a new object will be created. The obj
1394        model class is defided at obj_dict['model_class'] and if not defined an
1395        PumpWoodObjectSavingException will be raised.
1396
1397        Args:
1398          obj_dict (dict): Model data dictionary. It must have 'model_class'
1399                           key and if 'pk' key is not defined a new object will
1400                           be created, else object with pk will be updated.
1401        Kwargs:
1402          files (dict): A dictionary of files to be added to as a multi-part
1403                        post request.
1404          auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.
1405        Returns:
1406          dict: Updated/Created object data.
1407        Raises:
1408          PumpWoodObjectSavingException(
1409              'To save an object obj_dict must have model_class defined.'):
1410            Will be raised if model_class key is not present on
1411            obj_dict dictionary
1412        Example:
1413          No example yet.
1414
1415        """
1416        model_class = obj_dict.get('model_class')
1417        if model_class is None:
1418            raise PumpWoodObjectSavingException(
1419                'To save an object obj_dict must have model_class defined.')
1420
1421        url_str = self._build_save_url(model_class)
1422        return self.request_post(
1423            url=url_str, data=obj_dict, files=files,
1424            auth_header=auth_header)
1425
1426    @staticmethod
1427    def _build_save_streaming_file_url(model_class, pk):
1428        return "rest/{model_class}/save-file-streaming/{pk}/".format(
1429            model_class=model_class.lower(), pk=pk)
1430
1431    def save_streaming_file(self, model_class: str, pk: int, file_field: str,
1432                            file: io.BufferedReader, file_name: str = None,
1433                            auth_header: dict = None):
1434        """
1435        Stream file to PumpWood.
1436
1437        Args:
1438            model_class (str): Model class of the object.
1439            pk (int): pk of the object.
1440            file_field (str): File field that will receive file stream.
1441            file (io.BufferedReader): File to upload.
1442
1443        Kwargs:
1444            file_name (str): Name of the file, is not set it will be saved as
1445                {pk}__{file_field}.{extension at permited extension}
1446            auth_header (dict): Authentication dictionary.
1447        """
1448        request_header = self._check__auth_header(auth_header=auth_header)
1449        request_header["Content-Type"] = "application/octet-stream"
1450        post_url = self.server_url + self._build_save_streaming_file_url(
1451            model_class=model_class, pk=pk)
1452
1453        parameters = {}
1454        parameters["file_field"] = file_field
1455        if file_name is not None:
1456            parameters["file_name"] = file_name
1457
1458        response = requests.post(
1459            url=post_url, data=file, params=parameters,
1460            verify=self.verify_ssl, headers=request_header, stream=True)
1461
1462        file_last_bite = file.tell()
1463        self.error_handler(response)
1464        json_response = PumpWoodMicroService.angular_json(response)
1465
1466        if file_last_bite != json_response["bytes_uploaded"]:
1467            template = "Saved bytes in streaming [{}] differ from file " + \
1468                "bites [{}]."
1469            raise PumpWoodException(
1470                    template.format(
1471                        json_response["bytes_uploaded"], file_last_bite))
1472        return json_response["file_path"]

1727    def fill_validation(self, model_class: str, parcial_obj_dict: dict = {},
1728                        field: str = None, auth_header: dict = None,
1729                        user_type: str = 'api'):
1730        """
1731        Return options for object fields.
1732
1733        This function send partial object data and return options to finish
1734        object fillment.
1735
1736        Args:
1737          model_class (str): Model class to check filment options.
1738        Kwargs:
1739          parcial_obj_dict (dict): Partial object data
1740          field (str): Get an specific field information
1741          auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.
1742        Returns:
1743          dict: Dictionary with possible data.
1744        Raises:
1745          Dependends on backend implementation
1746        Example:
1747          No example yet.
1748        """
1749        url_str = "rest/{basename}/retrieve-options/".format(
1750            basename=model_class.lower())
1751        params = {"user_type": user_type}
1752        if field is not None:
1753            params["field"] = field
1754        return self.request_post(
1755            url=url_str, auth_header=auth_header, data=parcial_obj_dict,
1756            parameters=params)
1757
1758    @staticmethod
1759    def _build_pivot_url(model_class):
1760        return "rest/%s/pivot/" % (model_class.lower(), )
1761
1762    def pivot(self, model_class: str, columns: list = [], format: str = 'list',
1763              filter_dict: dict = {}, exclude_dict: dict = {},
1764              order_by: list = [], variables: list = None,
1765              show_deleted=False, auth_header: dict = None):
1766        """
1767        Pivot object data acording to columns specified.
1768
1769        Args:
1770            model_class (str): Model class to be pivoted.
1771        Kwargs:
1772            columns (str): Fields to be used as columns.
1773            format (str): Format to be used to convert pandas.DataFrame to
1774                          dictionary, must be in ['dict','list','series',
1775                          'split', 'records','index'].
1776            filter_dict (dict): Dictionary to to be used in objects.filter
1777                                argument (Same as list end-point).
1778            exclude_dict (dict): Dictionary to to be used in objects.exclude
1779                                 argument (Same as list end-point).
1780            order_by (list): Dictionary to to be used in objects.order_by
1781                             argument (Same as list end-point).
1782            variables (list[str]) = None: List of the variables to be returned,
1783                if None, the default variables will be returned.
1784            show_deleted (bool): If deleted data should be returned.
1785            auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.
1786        Returns:
1787            dict or list: Depends on format type used to convert
1788                          pandas.DataFrame
1789        Raises:
1790            Dependends on backend implementation
1791        Example:
1792            No example yet.
1793        """
1794        url_str = self._build_pivot_url(model_class)
1795        post_data = {
1796            'columns': columns, 'format': format,
1797            'filter_dict': filter_dict, 'exclude_dict': exclude_dict,
1798            'order_by': order_by, "variables": variables,
1799            "show_deleted": show_deleted}
1800        return self.request_post(
1801            url=url_str, data=post_data, auth_header=auth_header)
1802
1803    def _flat_list_by_chunks_helper(self, args):
1804        try:
1805            # Unpacking arguments
1806            model_class = args["model_class"]
1807            filter_dict = args["filter_dict"]
1808            exclude_dict = args["exclude_dict"]
1809            fields = args["fields"]
1810            show_deleted = args["show_deleted"]
1811            auth_header = args["auth_header"]
1812            chunk_size = args["chunk_size"]
1813
1814            temp_filter_dict = copy.deepcopy(filter_dict)
1815            url_str = self._build_pivot_url(model_class)
1816            max_pk = 0
1817
1818            # Fetch data until an empty result is returned
1819            list_dataframes = []
1820            while True:
1821                sys.stdout.write(".")
1822                sys.stdout.flush()
1823                temp_filter_dict["id__gt"] = max_pk
1824                post_data = {
1825                    'format': 'list',
1826                    'filter_dict': temp_filter_dict,
1827                    'exclude_dict': exclude_dict,
1828                    'order_by': ["id"], "variables": fields,
1829                    "show_deleted": show_deleted,
1830                    "limit": chunk_size,
1831                    "add_pk_column": True}
1832                temp_dateframe = pd.DataFrame(self.request_post(
1833                    url=url_str, data=post_data, auth_header=auth_header))
1834
1835                # Break if results are less than chunk size, so no more results
1836                # are avaiable
1837                if len(temp_dateframe) < chunk_size:
1838                    list_dataframes.append(temp_dateframe)
1839                    break
1840
1841                max_pk = int(temp_dateframe["id"].max())
1842                list_dataframes.append(temp_dateframe)
1843
1844            if len(list_dataframes) == 0:
1845                return pd.DataFrame()
1846            else:
1847                return pd.concat(list_dataframes)
1848        except Exception as e:
1849            raise Exception("Exception at flat_list_by_chunks:", str(e))
1850
1851    def flat_list_by_chunks(self, model_class: str, filter_dict: dict = {},
1852                            exclude_dict: dict = {}, fields: list = None,
1853                            show_deleted: bool = False,
1854                            auth_header: dict = None,
1855                            chunk_size: int = 1000000,
1856                            n_parallel: int = None,
1857                            create_composite_pk: bool = False,
1858                            start_date: str = None,
1859                            end_date: str = None):
1860        """
1861        Use the same end-point as pivot which does not unserialize results.
1862
1863        Args:
1864            model_class (str): Model class to be pivoted.
1865
1866        Kwargs:
1867            filter_dict (dict): Dictionary to to be used in objects.filter
1868                                argument (Same as list end-point).
1869            exclude_dict (dict): Dictionary to to be used in objects.exclude
1870                                 argument (Same as list end-point).
1871            fields (list[str]) = None: List of the variables to be returned,
1872                if None, the default variables will be returned.
1873            show_deleted (bool): If deleted data should be returned.
1874            auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.
1875            chunk_size (int): Limit of data to fetch per call.
1876            n_parallel (int): Number of parallel process to perform.
1877
1878        Returns:
1879            dict or list: Depends on format type used to convert
1880                          pandas.DataFrame
1881
1882        Raises:
1883            Dependends on backend implementation
1884
1885        Example:
1886            No example yet.
1887        """
1888        if n_parallel is None:
1889            n_parallel = int(os.getenv(
1890                "PUMPWOOD_COMUNICATION__N_PARALLEL", 4))
1891
1892        temp_filter_dict = copy.deepcopy(filter_dict)
1893        fill_options = self.fill_options(
1894            model_class=model_class, auth_header=auth_header)
1895        primary_keys = fill_options["pk"]["column"]
1896        partition = fill_options["pk"].get("partition", [])
1897
1898        # Create a list of month and include start and end dates if not at
1899        # the beginning of a month
1900        month_sequence = None
1901        if (start_date is not None) and (end_date is not None):
1902            start_date = pd.to_datetime(start_date)
1903            end_date = pd.to_datetime(end_date)
1904            list_month_sequence = pd.date_range(
1905                start=start_date, end=end_date, freq='MS').tolist()
1906            month_sequence = pd.Series(
1907                [start_date] + list_month_sequence + [end_date]
1908            ).sort_values().tolist()
1909
1910            month_df = pd.DataFrame({'end': month_sequence})
1911            month_df['start'] = month_df['end'].shift()
1912            month_df = month_df.dropna().drop_duplicates()
1913            month_sequence = month_df.to_dict("records")
1914        elif (start_date is not None) or (end_date is not None):
1915            msg = (
1916                "To break query in chunks using start_date and end_date "
1917                "both must be set.\n"
1918                "start_date: {start_date}\n"
1919                "end_date: {end_date}\n").format(
1920                    start_date=start_date, end_date=end_date)
1921            raise PumpWoodException(
1922                message=msg, payload={
1923                    "start_date": start_date,
1924                    "end_date": end_date})
1925
1926        resp_df = pd.DataFrame()
1927        ##########################################################
1928        # If table have more than one partition, run in parallel #
1929        # the {partition}__in elements along with dates          #
1930        if 1 < len(partition):
1931            partition_col_1st = partition[0]
1932            filter_dict_keys = list(temp_filter_dict.keys())
1933            partition_filter = None
1934            count_partition_col_1st_filters = 0
1935            for col in filter_dict_keys:
1936                if partition_col_1st + "__in" == col:
1937                    partition_filter = temp_filter_dict[col]
1938                    del temp_filter_dict[col]
1939                    count_partition_col_1st_filters = \
1940                        count_partition_col_1st_filters + 1
1941                elif partition_col_1st == col:
1942                    partition_filter = [temp_filter_dict[col]]
1943                    del temp_filter_dict[col]
1944                    count_partition_col_1st_filters = \
1945                        count_partition_col_1st_filters + 1
1946
1947            # Validating query for partitioned tables
1948            if partition_filter is None:
1949                msg = (
1950                    "Table is partitioned with sub-partitions, running "
1951                    "queries without at least first level partition will "
1952                    "lead to long waiting times or hanging queries. Please "
1953                    "use first partition level in filter_dict with equal "
1954                    "or in operators. Table partitions: {}"
1955                ).format(partition)
1956                raise PumpWoodException(message=msg)
1957
1958            if 1 < count_partition_col_1st_filters:
1959                msg = (
1960                    "Please give some help for the dev here, use just one "
1961                    "filter_dict entry for first partition...")
1962                raise PumpWoodException(message=msg)
1963
1964            # Parallelizing query using partition columns
1965            pool_arguments = []
1966            for filter_key in partition_filter:
1967                request_filter_dict = copy.deepcopy(temp_filter_dict)
1968                request_filter_dict[partition_col_1st] = filter_key
1969                if month_sequence is None:
1970                    pool_arguments.append({
1971                        "model_class": model_class,
1972                        "filter_dict": request_filter_dict,
1973                        "exclude_dict": exclude_dict,
1974                        "fields": fields,
1975                        "show_deleted": show_deleted,
1976                        "auth_header": auth_header,
1977                        "chunk_size": chunk_size})
1978                else:
1979                    for i in range(len(month_sequence)):
1980                        request_filter_dict_t = copy.deepcopy(
1981                            request_filter_dict)
1982                        # If is not the last interval, query using open
1983                        # right interval so subsequence querys does
1984                        # not overlap
1985                        if i != len(month_sequence) - 1:
1986                            request_filter_dict_t["time__gte"] = \
1987                                month_sequence[i]["start"]
1988                            request_filter_dict_t["time__lt"] = \
1989                                month_sequence[i]["end"]
1990
1991                        # At the last interaval use closed right interval so
1992                        # last element is also included in the interval
1993                        else:
1994                            request_filter_dict_t["time__gte"] = \
1995                                month_sequence[i]["start"]
1996                            request_filter_dict_t["time__lte"] = \
1997                                month_sequence[i]["end"]
1998
1999                        pool_arguments.append({
2000                            "model_class": model_class,
2001                            "filter_dict": request_filter_dict_t,
2002                            "exclude_dict": exclude_dict,
2003                            "fields": fields,
2004                            "show_deleted": show_deleted,
2005                            "auth_header": auth_header,
2006                            "chunk_size": chunk_size})
2007
2008            # Perform parallel calls to backend each chucked by chunk_size
2009            print("## Starting parallel flat list: %s" % len(pool_arguments))
2010            try:
2011                with Pool(n_parallel) as p:
2012                    results = p.map(
2013                        self._flat_list_by_chunks_helper,
2014                        pool_arguments)
2015                resp_df = pd.concat(results)
2016            except Exception as e:
2017                PumpWoodException(message=str(e))
2018            print("\n## Finished parallel flat list: %s" % len(pool_arguments))
2019
2020        ############################################
2021        # If table have partition, run in parallel #
2022        else:
2023            try:
2024                results_key_data = self._flat_list_by_chunks_helper({
2025                    "model_class": model_class,
2026                    "filter_dict": temp_filter_dict,
2027                    "exclude_dict": exclude_dict,
2028                    "fields": fields,
2029                    "show_deleted": show_deleted,
2030                    "auth_header": auth_header,
2031                    "chunk_size": chunk_size})
2032                resp_df = results_key_data
2033            except Exception as e:
2034                PumpWoodException(message=str(e))
2035
2036        if (1 < len(partition)) and create_composite_pk:
2037            print("## Creating composite pk")
2038            resp_df["pk"] = resp_df[primary_keys].apply(
2039                CompositePkBase64Converter.dump,
2040                primary_keys=primary_keys, axis=1)
2041        return resp_df
2042

2075    @staticmethod
2076    def flatten_parallel(parallel_result: list):
2077        """
2078        Concat all parallel return to one list.
2079
2080        Args:
2081            parallel_result (list): A list of lists to be flated (concatenate
2082                all lists into one).
2083        Return:
2084            A list with all sub list itens.
2085        """
2086        return [
2087            item for sublist in parallel_result
2088            for item in sublist]

2090    def parallel_request_get(self, urls_list: list, n_parallel: int = None,
2091                             auth_header: dict = None):
2092        """
2093        Make many [n_parallel] get request.
2094
2095        Args:
2096            urls_list (list): List of urls to make get requests.
2097        Kwargs:
2098            n_parallel (int): Number of simultaneus get requests, if not set
2099                get from PUMPWOOD_COMUNICATION__N_PARALLEL env variable, if
2100                not set then 4 will be considered.
2101            auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.
2102        Returns:
2103            list: List of the get request reponses.
2104        Raises:
2105            No particular raises
2106        Example:
2107            No example yet.
2108
2109        """
2110        if n_parallel is None:
2111            n_parallel = int(os.getenv(
2112                "PUMPWOOD_COMUNICATION__N_PARALLEL", 4))
2113
2114        pool_arguments = [
2115            {'url': u, 'auth_header': auth_header} for u in urls_list]
2116
2117        with Pool(n_parallel) as p:
2118            results = p.map(self._request_get_wrapper, pool_arguments)
2119        print("|")
2120        return results

2131    def paralell_request_post(self, urls_list: list, data_list: list,
2132                              n_parallel: int = None,
2133                              auth_header: dict = None):
2134        """
2135        Make many [n_parallel] post request.
2136
2137        Args:
2138            urls_list (list<str>): List of urls to make get requests.
2139            data_list (list<any>): List of data to be used as post payloads.
2140        Kwargs:
2141            n_parallel (int): Number of simultaneus get requests, if not set
2142                get from PUMPWOOD_COMUNICATION__N_PARALLEL env variable, if
2143                not set then 4 will be considered.
2144            auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.
2145        Returns:
2146            list: List of the post request reponses.
2147        Raises:
2148            No particular raises
2149        Example:
2150            No example yet.
2151
2152        """
2153        if len(urls_list) != len(data_list):
2154            raise Exception(
2155                'len(urls_list) must be equal to len(data_list)')
2156
2157        pool_arguments = []
2158        for i in range(len(urls_list)):
2159            pool_arguments.append(
2160                {'url': urls_list[i], 'data': data_list[i],
2161                 'auth_header': auth_header})
2162
2163        with Pool(n_parallel) as p:
2164            results = p.map(self._request_post_wrapper, pool_arguments)
2165        print("|")
2166        return results

2207    def parallel_retrieve(self, model_class: Union[str, List[str]],
2208                          list_pk: List[int], n_parallel: int = None,
2209                          auth_header: dict = None):
2210        """
2211        Make many [n_parallel] retrieve request.
2212
2213        Args:
2214            model_class (str, List[str]): Model Class to retrieve.
2215            list_pk (List[int]): List of the pks to retrieve.
2216        Kwargs:
2217            n_parallel (int): Number of simultaneus get requests, if not set
2218                get from PUMPWOOD_COMUNICATION__N_PARALLEL env variable, if
2219                not set then 4 will be considered.
2220            auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.
2221        Returns:
2222            list: List of the retrieve request reponses.
2223        Raises:
2224            No particular raises
2225        Example:
2226            No example yet.
2227
2228        """
2229        if n_parallel is None:
2230            n_parallel = int(os.getenv(
2231                "PUMPWOOD_COMUNICATION__N_PARALLEL", 4))
2232
2233        if type(model_class) != list:
2234            model_class = [model_class]*len(list_pk)
2235
2236        if len(model_class) != len(list_pk):
2237            raise Exception('len(model_class) != len(list_pk)')
2238
2239        urls_list = [
2240            self._build_retrieve_url(model_class=model_class[i],
2241                                     pk=list_pk[i])
2242            for i in range(len(model_class))]
2243        return self.parallel_request_get(
2244            urls_list=urls_list, n_parallel=n_parallel,
2245            auth_header=auth_header)
