2247    def _request_retrieve_file_wrapper(self, args):
2248        sys.stdout.write(".")
2249        sys.stdout.flush()
2250        try:
2251            return self.retrieve_file(**args)
2252        except Exception as e:
2253            raise Exception("Error in parallel retrieve_file: " + str(e))
2254
2255    def parallel_retrieve_file(self, model_class: str,
2256                               list_pk: List[int], file_field: str = None,
2257                               save_path: str = "./", save_file: bool = True,
2258                               list_file_name: List[str] = None,
2259                               if_exists: str = "fail",
2260                               n_parallel: int = None,
2261                               auth_header: dict = None):
2262        """
2263        Make many [n_parallel] retrieve request.
2264
2265        Args:
2266            model_class (str, List[str]): Model Class to retrieve.
2267            list_pk (List[int]): List of the pks to retrieve.
2268            file_field (str): Indicates the file field to download from.
2269        Kwargs:
2270            n_parallel (int): Number of simultaneus get requests, if not set
2271                get from PUMPWOOD_COMUNICATION__N_PARALLEL env variable, if
2272                not set then 4 will be considered.
2273            save_path (str) = "./"
2274            save_file (bool) = True: True save file locally, False return
2275                file content as bites.
2276            list_file_name (List[str]) = None: Set a file name for each file
2277                download.
2278            if_exists (str) = "fail": Set how treat when a file will be saved
2279                and there is another at same path. "fail" will raise an error;
2280                "overwrite" will overwrite the file with the new one; "skip"
2281                when list_file_name is set, check before downloaded it file
2282                already exists, if so skip the download.
2283            auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.
2284
2285        Returns:
2286            list: List of the retrieve request reponses.
2287        Raises:
2288            No particular raises
2289        Example:
2290            No example yet.
2291
2292        """
2293        if n_parallel is None:
2294            n_parallel = int(os.getenv(
2295                "PUMPWOOD_COMUNICATION__N_PARALLEL", 4))
2296
2297        if list_file_name is not None:
2298            if len(list_file_name) != len(list_pk):
2299                raise PumpWoodException((
2300                    "Lenght of list_file_name and list_pk are not equal:\n"
2301                    "len(list_file_name)={list_file_name}; "
2302                    "len(list_pk)={list_pk}").format(
2303                        list_file_name=len(list_file_name),
2304                        list_pk=len(list_pk)))
2305
2306        pool_arguments = []
2307        for i in range(len(list_pk)):
2308            pk = list_pk[i]
2309            file_name = None
2310            if list_file_name is not None:
2311                file_name = list_file_name[i]
2312
2313            pool_arguments.append({
2314                "model_class": model_class, "pk": pk,
2315                "file_field": file_field, "auth_header": auth_header,
2316                "save_file": save_file, "file_name": file_name,
2317                "save_path": save_path, "if_exists": if_exists})
2318
2319        try:
2320            with Pool(n_parallel) as p:
2321                results = p.map(
2322                    self._request_retrieve_file_wrapper,
2323                    pool_arguments)
2324            print("|")
2325        except Exception as e:
2326            raise PumpWoodException(str(e))
2327
2328        return results
2329
2330    def parallel_list(self, model_class: Union[str, List[str]],
2331                      list_args: List[dict], n_parallel: int = None,
2332                      auth_header: dict = None):
2333        """
2334        Make many [n_parallel] list request.
2335
2336        Args:
2337            model_class (str): Model Class to retrieve.
2338            list_args_list (list): A list of list request args (filter_dict,
2339                                   exclude_dict, order_by).
2340        Kwargs:
2341            n_parallel (int): Number of simultaneus get requests, if not set
2342                get from PUMPWOOD_COMUNICATION__N_PARALLEL env variable, if
2343                not set then 4 will be considered.
2344            auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.
2345        Returns:
2346            list: List of the retrieve request reponses.
2347        Raises:
2348            No particular raises
2349        Example:
2350            No example yet.
2351
2352        """
2353        if n_parallel is None:
2354            n_parallel = int(os.getenv(
2355                "PUMPWOOD_COMUNICATION__N_PARALLEL", 4))
2356
2357        urls_list = None
2358        if type(model_class) == str:
2359            urls_list = [self._build_list_url(model_class)]*len(list_args)
2360        else:
2361            if len(model_class) != len(list_args):
2362                raise Exception('len(model_class) != len(list_args)')

2576    def parallel_execute_action(self, model_class: Union[str, List[str]],
2577                                pk: Union[int, List[int]],
2578                                action: Union[str, List[str]],
2579                                parameters: Union[dict, List[dict]] = {},
2580                                n_parallel: int = None,
2581                                auth_header: dict = None):
2582        """
2583        Make many [n_parallel] execute_action requests.
2584
2585        Args:
2586            model_class (str, list(str)): Model Class to perform action over,
2587                or a list of model class o make diferent actions.
2588            pk (int, list[int]): A list of the pks to perform action or a
2589                single pk to perform action with different paraemters.
2590            action (str, list[str]): A list of actions to perform or a single
2591                action to perform over all pks and parameters.
2592        Kwargs:
2593            parameters (dict, list[dict]): Parameters used to perform actions
2594                or a single dict to be used in all actions.
2595            n_parallel (int): Number of simultaneus get requests, if not set
2596                get from PUMPWOOD_COMUNICATION__N_PARALLEL env variable, if
2597                not set then 4 will be considered.
2598            auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.
2599        Returns:
2600            list: List of the retrieve request reponses.
2601        Raises:
2602            No particular raises
2603        Example:
2604            No example yet.
2605
2606        """
2607        if n_parallel is None:
2608            n_parallel = int(os.getenv(
2609                "PUMPWOOD_COMUNICATION__N_PARALLEL", 4))
2610
2611        parallel_length = None
2612        if type(model_class) == list:
2613            if parallel_length is not None:
2614                if parallel_length != len(model_class):
2615                    raise Exception('parallel_length != len(model_class)')
2616            else:
2617                parallel_length = len(model_class)
2618        if type(pk) == list:
2619            if parallel_length is not None:
2620                if parallel_length != len(pk):
2621                    raise Exception('parallel_length != len(pk)')
2622            else:
2623                parallel_length = len(pk)
2624        if type(action) == list:
2625            if parallel_length is not None:
2626                if parallel_length != len(action):
2627                    raise Exception('parallel_length != len(action)')
2628            else:
2629                parallel_length = len(action)
2630        if type(parameters) == list:
2631            if parallel_length is not None:
2632                if parallel_length != len(parameters):
2633                    raise Exception('parallel_length != len(parameters)')
2634            else:
2635                parallel_length = len(parameters)
2636
2637        model_class = model_class if type(model_class) == list \
2638            else [model_class]*parallel_length
2639        pk = pk if type(pk) == list \
2640            else [pk]*parallel_length
2641        action = action if type(action) == list \
2642            else [action]*parallel_length
2643        parameters = parameters if type(parameters) == list \
2644            else [parameters]*parallel_length
2645
2646        urls_list = [
2647            self._build_execute_action_url(
2648                model_class=model_class[i], action=action[i], pk=pk[i])
2649            for i in range(parallel_length)]
2650
2651        print("## Starting parallel_execute_action: %s" % len(urls_list))
2652        return self.paralell_request_post(
2653            urls_list=urls_list, data_list=parameters,
2654            n_parallel=n_parallel, auth_header=auth_header)

2659        """

2678

2680                                 chunksize=chunksize)
2681        url = self._build_bulk_save_url(model_class)
2682        urls_list = [url]*len(chunks)
2683
2684        print("## Starting parallel_bulk_save: %s" % len(urls_list))

2734    def get_queue_matrix(self, queue_pk: int, auth_header: dict = None,
2735                         save_as_excel: str = None):
2736        """Download model queue estimation matrix."""
2737        file_content = self.retrieve_file(
2738            model_class="ModelQueue", pk=queue_pk,
2739            file_field="model_matrix_file", auth_header=auth_header,
2740            save_file=False)
2741        content = gzip.GzipFile(
2742            fileobj=io.BytesIO(file_content["content"])).read()
2743        data = json.loads(content.decode('utf-8'))
2744        columns_info = pd.DataFrame(data["columns_info"])
2745        model_matrix = pd.DataFrame(data["model_matrix"])
2746
2747        if save_as_excel is not None:
2748            writer = ExcelWriter(save_as_excel)
2749            columns_info.to_excel(writer, 'columns_info', index=False)
2750            model_matrix.to_excel(writer, 'model_matrix', index=False)
2751            writer.save()
2752        else:
2753            return {
2754                "columns_info": columns_info,
2755                "model_matrix": model_matrix}

140        """
141        Convert text to Json removing any XSSI at the beging of JSON.
142
143        Args:

145        Kwargs:

155            return None
156
157        string_start = ")]}',\n"

159            if request_result.text[:6] == string_start:
160                return (json.loads(request_result.text[6:]))
161            else:
162                return (json.loads(request_result.text))
163        except Exception:
164            return {"error": "Can not decode to Json",
165                    'msg': request_result.text}

def time_to_expiry(self) -> pandas._libs.tslibs.timedeltas.Timedelta: 
167    def time_to_expiry(self) -> pd.Timedelta:
168        """
169        Return time to token expiry.
170
171        Args:
172            No Args.
173        Kwargs:
174            No Kwargs.
175        Return:
176            Return time until token expiration.
177        """
178        if self.__token_expiry is None:
179            return None
180
181        now_datetime = pd.to_datetime(datetime.datetime.utcnow(), utc=True)
182        time_to_expiry = self.__token_expiry - now_datetime
183        return time_to_expiry

def login(self, force_refresh: bool = False) -> None: 
199    def login(self, force_refresh: bool = False) -> None:
200        """
201        Log microservice in using username and password provided.
202
203        Args:
204            No Args.
205        Kwargs:
206            force_refresh [bool]: Force token refresh despise still valid
207                according to self.__token_expiry.
208        Returns:
209            No return
210        Raises:
211            Exception: If login response has status diferent from 200.
212        Example:
213            No example
214
215        """
216        if not self.is_credential_set():
217            raise PumpWoodUnauthorized(
218                message="Microservice username or/and password not set")
219
220        # Check if expiry time is 1h from now
221        refresh_expiry = False
222        if self.__token_expiry is None:
223            refresh_expiry = True
224        else:
225            time_to_expiry = self.time_to_expiry()
226            if time_to_expiry < datetime.timedelta(hours=1):
227                refresh_expiry = True
228
229        # When if debug always refresh token
230        is_debug = None
231        if self.debug is None:
232            is_debug = os.getenv("DEBUG", "FALSE") == "TRUE"
233        else:
234            is_debug = self.debug
235
236        if refresh_expiry or force_refresh or is_debug:
237            login_url = None
238            if self.auth_suffix is None:
239                login_url = urljoin(
240                    self.server_url, 'rest/registration/login/')
241            else:
242                temp_url = 'rest/{suffix}registration/login/'.format(
243                    suffix=self.auth_suffix.lower())
244                login_url = urljoin(self.server_url, temp_url)
245
246            login_result = requests.post(
247                login_url, json={
248                    'username': self.__username,
249                    'password': self.__password},
250                verify=self.verify_ssl)
251
252            login_data = {}
253            try:
254                login_data = PumpWoodMicroService.angular_json(login_result)
255                login_result.raise_for_status()
256            except Exception as e:
257                raise PumpWoodUnauthorized(
258                    message="Login not possible.\nError: " + str(e),
259                    payload=login_data)
260
261            if 'mfa_token' in login_data.keys():
262                login_data = self.confirm_mfa_code(mfa_login_data=login_data)
263
264            self.__auth_header = {
265                'Authorization': 'Token ' + login_data['token']}
266            self.__user = login_data["user"]
267            self.__token_expiry = pd.to_datetime(login_data['expiry'])

Log microservice in using username and password provided.

Arguments:
  • No Args.
Kwargs:

force_refresh [bool]: Force token refresh despise still valid according to self.__token_expiry.

Returns:

No return

Raises:
  • Exception: If login response has status diferent from 200.
Example:

No example

def error_handler(cls, response): 
433    def error_handler(cls, response):
434        """
435        Handle request error.
436
437        Check if is a Json and propagate the error with
438        same type if possible. If not Json raises the content.
439
440        Arg:
441            response (Response): response to be handled.
442        Kwargs:
443            No kwargs.
444        Returns:
445            No return.
446        Raises:
447            Exception: If content-type is not application/json.
448            Exception: If content-type is application/json, but type not
449                       present or not recognisable.
450            Other Exception: If content-type is application/json if type is
451                             present and recognisable.
452        Example:
453            No example
454
455        """
456        if not response.ok:
457            utcnow = datetime.datetime.utcnow()
458            response_content_type = response.headers['content-type']
459
460            # Request information
461            url = response.url
462            method = response.request.method
463            if 'application/json' not in response_content_type.lower():
464                # Raise the exception as first in exception deep.
465                exception_dict = [{
466                    "exception_url": url,
467                    "exception_method": method,
468                    "exception_utcnow": utcnow.isoformat(),
469                    "exception_deep": 1}]
470                raise PumpWoodOtherException(
471                    message=response.text, payload={
472                        "!exception_stack!": exception_dict})
473
474            # Build error stack
475            response_dict = PumpWoodMicroService.angular_json(response)
476
477            # Removing previus error stack
478            payload = deepcopy(response_dict.get("payload", {}))
479            exception_stack = deepcopy(payload.pop("!exception_stack!", []))
480
481            exception_deep = len(exception_stack)
482            exception_dict = {
483                "exception_url": url,
484                "exception_method": method,
485                "exception_utcnow": utcnow.isoformat(),
486                "exception_deep": exception_deep + 1
487            }
488            exception_stack.insert(0, exception_dict)
489            payload["!exception_stack!"] = exception_stack
490
491            # Propagate error
492            exception_message = response_dict.get("message", "")
493            exception_type = response_dict.get("type", None)
494            if exception_type is not None:
495                raise exceptions_dict[exception_type](
496                    message=exception_message,
497                    status_code=response.status_code,
498                    payload=payload)
499            else:
500                is_invalid_token = cls.is_invalid_token_response(response)
501                response_dict["!exception_stack!"] = exception_stack
502                if is_invalid_token:
503                    raise PumpWoodUnauthorized(
504                        message="Invalid token.",
505                        payload=response.json())
506                else:
507                    raise PumpWoodOtherException(
508                        message="Not mapped exception JSON",
509                        payload=response_dict)

Handle request error.

Check if is a Json and propagate the error with same type if possible. If not Json raises the content.

Arg:

response (Response): response to be handled.

Kwargs:

No kwargs.

Returns:

No return.

Raises:
  • Exception: If content-type is not application/json.
  • Exception: If content-type is application/json, but type not present or not recognisable.
  • Other Exception: If content-type is application/json if type is present and recognisable.
Example:

No example

def request_post( self, url: str, data: <built-in function any>, files: list = None, auth_header: dict = None, parameters: dict = {}): 
527    def request_post(self, url: str, data: any, files: list = None,
528                     auth_header: dict = None, parameters: dict = {}):
529        """
530        Make a POST a request to url with data as Json payload.
531
532        Args:
533            url (str): Url to make the request.
534            data (any); Data to be used as Json payload.
535        Kwargs:
536            files(list of tuples): A list of tuples with
537                                   (file name, [file1, file2, ...]).
538            params [dict]: Url parameters.
539            auth_header(dict): Auth data to overhide microservice's.
540        Returns:
541            any: Return the post result
542        Raises:
543            Response is passed to error_handler function.
544        Example:
545            No example
546
547        """
548        # If parameters are not none convert them to json before
549        # sending information on query string, 'True' is 'true' on javascript
550        # for exemple
551        if parameters is not None:
552            parameters = copy.deepcopy(parameters)
553            for key in parameters.keys():
554                # Do not convert str to json, it put extra "" araound string
555                if type(parameters[key]) is not str:
556                    parameters[key] = pumpJsonDump(parameters[key])
557
558        response = None
559        if files is None:
560            request_header = self._check__auth_header(auth_header=auth_header)
561            post_url = urljoin(self.server_url, url)
562            response = requests.post(
563                url=post_url, data=pumpJsonDump(data),
564                params=parameters, verify=self.verify_ssl,
565                headers=request_header)
566
567            # Retry request if token is not valid forcing token renew
568            retry_with_login = (
569                self.is_invalid_token_response(response) and
570                auth_header is None)
571            if retry_with_login:
572                self.login(force_refresh=True)
573                request_header = self._check__auth_header(
574                    auth_header=auth_header)
575                response = requests.post(
576                    url=post_url, data=pumpJsonDump(data),
577                    params=parameters, verify=self.verify_ssl,
578                    headers=request_header)
579
580        # Request with files are done using multipart serializing all fields
581        # as json
582        else:
583            request_header = self._check__auth_header(
584                auth_header=auth_header, multipart=True)
585            post_url = urljoin(self.server_url, url)
586            temp_data = {'__json__': pumpJsonDump(data)}
587            response = requests.post(
588                url=post_url, data=temp_data, files=files, params=parameters,
589                verify=self.verify_ssl, headers=request_header)
590
591            retry_with_login = (
592                self.is_invalid_token_response(response) and
593                auth_header is None)
594            if retry_with_login:
595                self.login(force_refresh=True)
596                request_header = self._check__auth_header(
597                    auth_header=auth_header)
598                response = requests.post(
599                    url=post_url, data=temp_data, files=files,
600                    params=parameters, verify=self.verify_ssl,
601                    headers=request_header)
602
603        # Handle errors and re-raise if Pumpwood Exceptions
604        self.error_handler(response)
605
606        # Check if reponse is a file
607        headers = response.headers
608        content_disposition = headers.get('content-disposition')
609        if content_disposition is not None:
610            file_name = re.findall('filename=(.+)', content_disposition)
611            if len(file_name) == 1:
612                return {
613                    "__file_name__": file_name[0],
614                    "__content__": response.content}
615            else:
616                return {
617                    "__file_name__": None,
618                    "__content__": response.content}
619        else:
620            return PumpWoodMicroService.angular_json(response)

Make a POST a request to url with data as Json payload.

Arguments:
  • url (str): Url to make the request.
  • data (any); Data to be used as Json payload.
Kwargs:

files(list of tuples): A list of tuples with (file name, [file1, file2, ...]). params [dict]: Url parameters. auth_header(dict): Auth data to overhide microservice's.

Returns:

any: Return the post result

Raises:
  • Response is passed to error_handler function.
Example:

No example

def request_get(self, url, parameters: dict = {}, auth_header: dict = None): 
622    def request_get(self, url, parameters: dict = {},
623                    auth_header: dict = None):
624        """
625        Make a GET a request to url with data as Json payload.
626
627        Args:
628            url (str): Url to make the request.
629        Kwargs:
630            parameters (dict): Url parameters to make the request.
631            auth_header (dict): Authentication dictionary.
632        Returns:
633            any: Return the post result
634        Raises:
635            Response is passed to error_handler function.
636        Example:
637            No example
638        """
639        request_header = self._check__auth_header(auth_header)
640
641        # If parameters are not none convert them to json before
642        # sending information on query string, 'True' is 'true' on javascript
643        # for example
644        if parameters is not None:
645            parameters = copy.deepcopy(parameters)
646            for key in parameters.keys():
647                # Do not convert str to json, it put extra "" araound string
648                if type(parameters[key]) is not str:
649                    parameters[key] = pumpJsonDump(parameters[key])
650
651        get_url = urljoin(self.server_url, url)
652        response = requests.get(
653            get_url, verify=self.verify_ssl, headers=request_header,
654            params=parameters)
655
656        retry_with_login = (
657            self.is_invalid_token_response(response) and
658            auth_header is None)
659        if retry_with_login:
660            self.login(force_refresh=True)
661            request_header = self._check__auth_header(auth_header=auth_header)
662            response = requests.get(
663                get_url, verify=self.verify_ssl, headers=request_header,
664                params=parameters)
665
666        # Re-raise Pumpwood exceptions
667        self.error_handler(response=response)
668
669        json_types = ["application/json", "application/json; charset=utf-8"]
670        if response.headers['content-type'] in json_types:
671            return PumpWoodMicroService.angular_json(response)
672        else:
673            d = response.headers['content-disposition']
674            fname = re.findall("filename=(.+)", d)[0]
675
676            return {
677                "content": response.content,
678                "content-type": response.headers['content-type'],
679                "filename": fname}

763                   auth_header: dict = None) -> dict:
764        """
765        Return a dummy call to ensure headers and payload reaching app.
766
767        Args:
768            No args.

788        if payload is None:
789            return self.request_get(
790                url=list_url, auth_header=auth_header)
791        else:
792            return self.request_post(
793                url=list_url, data=payload,
794                auth_header=auth_header)

def dummy_raise( self, exception_class: str, exception_deep: int, payload: dict = {}, auth_header: dict = None) -> None: 
796    def dummy_raise(self, exception_class: str, exception_deep: int,
797                    payload: dict = {}, auth_header: dict = None) -> None:
798        """
799        Raise an Pumpwood error with the payload.
800
801        Can be used for debug purposes.
802
803        Args:
804            exception_class (str): Class of the exception to be raised.
805            exception_deep (int): Deep of the exception in microservice
806                calls.
807        Kwards:
808            payload (dict]): Payload to be returned by the dummy call
809                end-point.
810            auth_header (dict): Auth header if microservice not logged.
811        Return:
812            Should not return any results, all possible call should result
813            in raising the correspondent error.
814        Exceptions:
815            Should raise the correspondent error passed on exception_class
816            arg, with payload.
817        """

820        payload["exception_deep"] = exception_deep
821        self.request_post(url=url, data=payload, auth_header=auth_header)

836            Return a dataframe in same order as values with columns:
837                - pk: correspondent primary key of the unique value.
838                - [field]: Column with same name of field argument,
839                    correspondent to pk.
840        """
841        is_dimension_tag = 'dimensions->' in field
842        if not is_dimension_tag:
843            fill_options = self.fill_options(model_class=model_class)
844            field_details = fill_options.get(field)
845            if field_details is None:
846                msg = (
847                    "Field is not a dimension tag and not found on model "
848                    "fields. Field [{field}]")
849                raise PumpWoodQueryException(
850                    message=msg, payload={"field": field})
851
852            is_unique_field = field_details.get("unique", False)
853            if not is_unique_field:
854                msg = "Field [{}] to get pk from is not unique"
855                raise PumpWoodQueryException(
856                    message=msg, payload={"field": field})
857
858        filter_dict = {field + "__in": list(set(values))}
859        pk_map = None
860        if not is_dimension_tag:
861            list_results = pd.DataFrame(self.list_without_pag(
862                model_class=model_class, filter_dict=filter_dict,
863                fields=["pk", field]), columns=["pk", field])
864            pk_map = list_results.set_index(field)["pk"]
865
866        # If is dimension tag, fetch dimension and unpack it
867        else:
868            dimension_tag = field.split("->")[1]
869            list_results = pd.DataFrame(self.list_without_pag(
870                model_class=model_class, filter_dict=filter_dict,
871                fields=["pk", "dimensions"]))
872            pk_map = {}
873            if len(list_results) != 0:
874                pk_map = list_results\
875                    .pipe(unpack_dict_columns, columns=["dimensions"])\
876                    .set_index(dimension_tag)["pk"]
877
878        values_series = pd.Series(values)
879        return pd.DataFrame({
880            "pk": values_series.map(pk_map).values,
881            field: values_series
882        })

937    def list_by_chunks(self, model_class: str, filter_dict: dict = {},

940                       chunk_size: int = 50000, **kwargs) -> list:
941        """
942        List object fetching them by chucks using pk to paginate.
943
944        List data by chunck to load by datasets without breaking the backend
945        or receive server timeout. It load chunks orderring the results using
946        id of the tables, it can be changed but it should be unique otherwise
947        unexpected results may occur.

949        Args:
950          model_class (str): Model class of the end-point
951
952        Kwargs:
953          filter_dict (dict) = {}: Filter dict to be used at the query
954            (objects.filter arguments).
955          exclude_dict (dict) = {}:  Exclude dict to be used at the query
956            (objects.exclude arguments).
957          auth_header (dict) = None: Dictionary containing the auth header.

966
967        Raises:
968          No especific raises.
969
970        Example:
971          No example yet.
972
973        """
974        copy_filter_dict = copy.deepcopy(filter_dict)
975
976        list_all_results = []
977        max_order_col = 0
978        while True:
979            print("- fetching chunk [{}]".format(max_order_col))
980            copy_filter_dict["pk__gt"] = max_order_col
981            temp_results = self.list(
982                model_class=model_class, filter_dict=copy_filter_dict,
983                exclude_dict=exclude_dict, order_by=["pk"],
984                auth_header=auth_header, fields=fields,
985                default_fields=default_fields, limit=chunk_size)
986
987            # Break if results is empty
988            if len(temp_results) == 0:
989                break
990
991            max_order_col = temp_results[-1]["pk"]
992            list_all_results.extend(temp_results)
993
994        return list_all_results

def retrieve_file( self, model_class: str, pk: int, file_field: str, auth_header: dict = None, save_file: bool = True, save_path: str = './', file_name: str = None, if_exists: str = 'fail'): 
1217    def retrieve_file(self, model_class: str, pk: int, file_field: str,
1218                      auth_header: dict = None, save_file: bool = True,
1219                      save_path: str = "./", file_name: str = None,
1220                      if_exists: str = "fail"):
1221        """
1222        Retrieve a file from PumpWood.
1223
1224        Args:
1225          model_class (str): Class of the model to retrieve file.
1226          pk (int): Pk of the object associeted file.
1227          file_field (str): Field of the file to be downloaded.
1228        Kwargs:
1229          auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.
1230          save_file (bool): If data is to be saved as file or return get
1231            response.
1232          save_path (str): Path of the directory to save file.
1233          file_name (str): Name of the file, if None it will have same name as
1234                saved in PumpWood.
1235          if_exists {'fail', 'change_name', 'overwrite', 'skip'}: Set what to
1236            do if there is a file with same name. Skip will not download file
1237            if there is already with same os.path.join(save_path, file_name),
1238            file_name must be set for skip argument.
1239        Returns:
1240          requset.response or str
1241        Raises:
1242          No especific raises.
1243        Example:
1244          No example yet.
1245
1246        """
1247        if if_exists not in ["fail", "change_name", "overwrite", "skip"]:
1248            raise PumpWoodException(
1249                "if_exists must be in ['fail', 'change_name', 'overwrite', "
1250                "'skip']")
1251
1252        if file_name is not None and if_exists == 'skip':
1253            file_path = os.path.join(save_path, file_name)
1254            is_file_already = os.path.isfile(file_path)
1255            if is_file_already:
1256                print("skiping file already exists: ", file_path)
1257                return file_path
1258
1259        url_str = self._build_retrieve_file_url(model_class=model_class, pk=pk)
1260        file_response = self.request_get(
1261            url=url_str, parameters={"file-field": file_field},
1262            auth_header=auth_header)
1263        if not save_file:
1264            return file_response
1265
1266        if not os.path.exists(save_path):
1267            raise PumpWoodException(
1268                "Path to save retrieved file [{}] does not exist".format(
1269                    save_path))
1270
1271        file_name = secure_filename(file_name or file_response["filename"])
1272        file_path = os.path.join(save_path, file_name)
1273        is_file_already = os.path.isfile(file_path)
1274        if is_file_already:
1275            if if_exists == "change_name":
1276                filename, file_extension = os.path.splitext(file_path)
1277                too_many_tries = True
1278                for i in range(10):
1279                    new_path = "{filename}__{count}{extension}".format(
1280                        filename=filename, count=i,
1281                        extension=file_extension)
1282                    if not os.path.isfile(new_path):
1283                        file_path = new_path
1284                        too_many_tries = False
1285                        break
1286                if too_many_tries:
1287                    raise PumpWoodException(
1288                        ("Too many tries to find a not used file name." +
1289                         " file_path[{}]".format(file_path)))
1290
1291            elif if_exists == "fail":
1292                raise PumpWoodException(
1293                    ("if_exists set as 'fail' and there is a file with same" +
1294                     "name. file_path [{}]").format(file_path))
1295
1296        with open(file_path, "wb") as file:
1297            file.write(file_response["content"])
1298        return file_path

1310        """
1311        Retrieve a file from PumpWood.
1312
1313        Args:
1314          model_class (str): Class of the model to retrieve file.
1315          pk (int): Pk of the object associeted file.
1316          file_field (str): Field of the file to be downloaded.
1317          file_name (str): Name of the file, if None it will have same name as
1318                saved in PumpWood.
1319
1320        Kwargs:
1321          auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.
1322          save_path (str): Path of the directory to save file.
1323          if_exists {'fail', 'change_name', 'overwrite'}: Set what to do if
1324            there is a file with same name.
1325
1326        Returns:
1327          requset.response or str
1328
1329        Raises:
1330          No especific raises.
1331
1332        Example:
1333          No example yet.
1334        """
1335        request_header = self._check__auth_header(auth_header)
1336
1337        # begin Args check
1338        if if_exists not in ["fail", "change_name", "overwrite"]:
1339            raise PumpWoodException(
1340                "if_exists must be in ['fail', 'change_name', 'overwrite']")
1341
1342        if not os.path.exists(save_path):
1343            raise PumpWoodException(
1344                "Path to save retrieved file [{}] does not exist".format(
1345                    save_path))
1346        # end Args check
1347
1348        file_path = os.path.join(save_path, file_name)
1349        if os.path.isfile(file_path) and if_exists == "change_name":
1350            filename, file_extension = os.path.splitext(file_path)
1351            too_many_tries = False
1352            for i in range(10):
1353                new_path = "{filename}__{count}{extension}".format(
1354                    filename=filename, count=i,
1355                    extension=file_extension)
1356                if not os.path.isfile(new_path):
1357                    file_path = new_path
1358                    too_many_tries = True
1359                    break
1360            if not too_many_tries:
1361                raise PumpWoodException(
1362                    ("Too many tries to find a not used file name." +
1363                     " file_path[{}]".format(file_path)))
1364
1365        if os.path.isfile(file_path) and if_exists == "fail":
1366            raise PumpWoodException(
1367                ("if_exists set as 'fail' and there is a file with same" +
1368                 "name. file_path [{}]").format(file_path))
1369
1370        url_str = self._build_retrieve_file_straming_url(
1371            model_class=model_class, pk=pk)
1372
1373        get_url = self.server_url + url_str
1374        with requests.get(
1375                get_url, verify=self.verify_ssl, headers=request_header,
1376                params={"file-field": file_field}) as response:
1377            self.error_handler(response)
1378            with open(file_path, 'wb') as f:
1379                for chunk in response.iter_content(chunk_size=8192):
1380                    if chunk:
1381                        f.write(chunk)
1382        return file_path

Retrieve a file from PumpWood.

Arguments:
  • model_class (str): Class of the model to retrieve file.
  • pk (int): Pk of the object associeted file.
  • file_field (str): Field of the file to be downloaded.
  • file_name (str): Name of the file, if None it will have same name as saved in PumpWood.
Kwargs:

auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header. save_path (str): Path of the directory to save file. if_exists {'fail', 'change_name', 'overwrite'}: Set what to do if there is a file with same name.

Returns:

requset.response or str

Raises:
  • No especific raises.
Example:

Save or Update a new object.

def save_streaming_file( self, model_class: str, pk: int, file_field: str, file: _io.BufferedReader, file_name: str = None, auth_header: dict = None): 
1431    def save_streaming_file(self, model_class: str, pk: int, file_field: str,
1432                            file: io.BufferedReader, file_name: str = None,
1433                            auth_header: dict = None):
1434        """
1435        Stream file to PumpWood.
1436
1437        Args:
1438            model_class (str): Model class of the object.
1439            pk (int): pk of the object.
1440            file_field (str): File field that will receive file stream.
1441            file (io.BufferedReader): File to upload.
1442
1443        Kwargs:
1444            file_name (str): Name of the file, is not set it will be saved as
1445                {pk}__{file_field}.{extension at permited extension}
1446            auth_header (dict): Authentication dictionary.
1447        """
1448        request_header = self._check__auth_header(auth_header=auth_header)
1449        request_header["Content-Type"] = "application/octet-stream"
1450        post_url = self.server_url + self._build_save_streaming_file_url(
1451            model_class=model_class, pk=pk)
1452
1453        parameters = {}
1454        parameters["file_field"] = file_field
1455        if file_name is not None:
1456            parameters["file_name"] = file_name
1457
1458        response = requests.post(
1459            url=post_url, data=file, params=parameters,
1460            verify=self.verify_ssl, headers=request_header, stream=True)
1461
1462        file_last_bite = file.tell()
1463        self.error_handler(response)
1464        json_response = PumpWoodMicroService.angular_json(response)
1465
1466        if file_last_bite != json_response["bytes_uploaded"]:
1467            template = "Saved bytes in streaming [{}] differ from file " + \
1468                "bites [{}]."
1469            raise PumpWoodException(
1470                    template.format(
1471                        json_response["bytes_uploaded"], file_last_bite))
1472        return json_response["file_path"]

Stream file to PumpWood.

  • pk (int): pk of the object.
  • file_field (str): File field that will receive file stream.
  • file (io.BufferedReader): File to upload.
Kwargs:

file_name (str): Name of the file, is not set it will be saved as {pk}__{file_field}.{extension at permited extension} auth_header (dict): Authentication dictionary.

columns (str): Fields to be used as columns. format (str): Format to be used to convert pandas.DataFrame to dictionary, must be in ['dict','list','series', 'split', 'records','index']. filter_dict (dict): Dictionary to to be used in objects.filter argument (Same as list end-point). exclude_dict (dict): Dictionary to to be used in objects.exclude argument (Same as list end-point). order_by (list): Dictionary to to be used in objects.order_by argument (Same as list end-point). variables (list[str]) = None: List of the variables to be returned, if None, the default variables will be returned. show_deleted (bool): If deleted data should be returned. auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.

Returns:

dict or list: Depends on format type used to convert pandas.DataFrame

Raises:
  • Dependends on backend implementation
Example:

def flat_list_by_chunks( self, model_class: str, filter_dict: dict = {}, exclude_dict: dict = {}, fields: <function PumpWoodMicroService.list> = None, show_deleted: bool = False, auth_header: dict = None, chunk_size: int = 1000000, n_parallel: int = None, create_composite_pk: bool = False, start_date: str = None, end_date: str = None): 
1851    def flat_list_by_chunks(self, model_class: str, filter_dict: dict = {},
1852                            exclude_dict: dict = {}, fields: list = None,
1853                            show_deleted: bool = False,
1854                            auth_header: dict = None,
1855                            chunk_size: int = 1000000,
1856                            n_parallel: int = None,
1857                            create_composite_pk: bool = False,
1858                            start_date: str = None,
1859                            end_date: str = None):
1860        """
1861        Use the same end-point as pivot which does not unserialize results.
1862
1863        Args:
1864            model_class (str): Model class to be pivoted.
1865
1866        Kwargs:
1867            filter_dict (dict): Dictionary to to be used in objects.filter
1868                                argument (Same as list end-point).
1869            exclude_dict (dict): Dictionary to to be used in objects.exclude
1870                                 argument (Same as list end-point).
1871            fields (list[str]) = None: List of the variables to be returned,
1872                if None, the default variables will be returned.
1873            show_deleted (bool): If deleted data should be returned.
1874            auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.
1875            chunk_size (int): Limit of data to fetch per call.
1876            n_parallel (int): Number of parallel process to perform.
1877
1878        Returns:
1879            dict or list: Depends on format type used to convert
1880                          pandas.DataFrame
1881
1882        Raises:
1883            Dependends on backend implementation
1884
1885        Example:
1886            No example yet.
1887        """
1888        if n_parallel is None:
1889            n_parallel = int(os.getenv(
1890                "PUMPWOOD_COMUNICATION__N_PARALLEL", 4))
1891
1892        temp_filter_dict = copy.deepcopy(filter_dict)
1893        fill_options = self.fill_options(
1894            model_class=model_class, auth_header=auth_header)
1895        primary_keys = fill_options["pk"]["column"]
1896        partition = fill_options["pk"].get("partition", [])
1897
1898        # Create a list of month and include start and end dates if not at
1899        # the beginning of a month
1900        month_sequence = None
1901        if (start_date is not None) and (end_date is not None):
1902            start_date = pd.to_datetime(start_date)
1903            end_date = pd.to_datetime(end_date)
1904            list_month_sequence = pd.date_range(
1905                start=start_date, end=end_date, freq='MS').tolist()
1906            month_sequence = pd.Series(
1907                [start_date] + list_month_sequence + [end_date]
1908            ).sort_values().tolist()
1909
1910            month_df = pd.DataFrame({'end': month_sequence})
1911            month_df['start'] = month_df['end'].shift()
1912            month_df = month_df.dropna().drop_duplicates()
1913            month_sequence = month_df.to_dict("records")
1914        elif (start_date is not None) or (end_date is not None):
1915            msg = (
1916                "To break query in chunks using start_date and end_date "
1917                "both must be set.\n"
1918                "start_date: {start_date}\n"
1919                "end_date: {end_date}\n").format(
1920                    start_date=start_date, end_date=end_date)
1921            raise PumpWoodException(
1922                message=msg, payload={
1923                    "start_date": start_date,
1924                    "end_date": end_date})
1925
1926        resp_df = pd.DataFrame()
1927        ##########################################################
1928        # If table have more than one partition, run in parallel #
1929        # the {partition}__in elements along with dates          #
1930        if 1 < len(partition):
1931            partition_col_1st = partition[0]
1932            filter_dict_keys = list(temp_filter_dict.keys())
1933            partition_filter = None
1934            count_partition_col_1st_filters = 0
1935            for col in filter_dict_keys:
1936                if partition_col_1st + "__in" == col:
1937                    partition_filter = temp_filter_dict[col]
1938                    del temp_filter_dict[col]
1939                    count_partition_col_1st_filters = \
1940                        count_partition_col_1st_filters + 1
1941                elif partition_col_1st == col:
1942                    partition_filter = [temp_filter_dict[col]]
1943                    del temp_filter_dict[col]
1944                    count_partition_col_1st_filters = \
1945                        count_partition_col_1st_filters + 1
1946
1947            # Validating query for partitioned tables
1948            if partition_filter is None:
1949                msg = (
1950                    "Table is partitioned with sub-partitions, running "
1951                    "queries without at least first level partition will "
1952                    "lead to long waiting times or hanging queries. Please "
1953                    "use first partition level in filter_dict with equal "
1954                    "or in operators. Table partitions: {}"
1955                ).format(partition)
1956                raise PumpWoodException(message=msg)
1957
1958            if 1 < count_partition_col_1st_filters:
1959                msg = (
1960                    "Please give some help for the dev here, use just one "
1961                    "filter_dict entry for first partition...")
1962                raise PumpWoodException(message=msg)
1963
1964            # Parallelizing query using partition columns
1965            pool_arguments = []
1966            for filter_key in partition_filter:
1967                request_filter_dict = copy.deepcopy(temp_filter_dict)
1968                request_filter_dict[partition_col_1st] = filter_key
1969                if month_sequence is None:
1970                    pool_arguments.append({
1971                        "model_class": model_class,
1972                        "filter_dict": request_filter_dict,
1973                        "exclude_dict": exclude_dict,
1974                        "fields": fields,
1975                        "show_deleted": show_deleted,
1976                        "auth_header": auth_header,
1977                        "chunk_size": chunk_size})
1978                else:
1979                    for i in range(len(month_sequence)):
1980                        request_filter_dict_t = copy.deepcopy(
1981                            request_filter_dict)
1982                        # If is not the last interval, query using open
1983                        # right interval so subsequence querys does
1984                        # not overlap
1985                        if i != len(month_sequence) - 1:
1986                            request_filter_dict_t["time__gte"] = \
1987                                month_sequence[i]["start"]
1988                            request_filter_dict_t["time__lt"] = \
1989                                month_sequence[i]["end"]
1990
1991                        # At the last interaval use closed right interval so
1992                        # last element is also included in the interval
1993                        else:
1994                            request_filter_dict_t["time__gte"] = \
1995                                month_sequence[i]["start"]
1996                            request_filter_dict_t["time__lte"] = \
1997                                month_sequence[i]["end"]
1998
1999                        pool_arguments.append({
2000                            "model_class": model_class,
2001                            "filter_dict": request_filter_dict_t,
2002                            "exclude_dict": exclude_dict,
2003                            "fields": fields,
2004                            "show_deleted": show_deleted,
2005                            "auth_header": auth_header,
2006                            "chunk_size": chunk_size})
2007
2008            # Perform parallel calls to backend each chucked by chunk_size
2009            print("## Starting parallel flat list: %s" % len(pool_arguments))
2010            try:
2011                with Pool(n_parallel) as p:
2012                    results = p.map(
2013                        self._flat_list_by_chunks_helper,
2014                        pool_arguments)
2015                resp_df = pd.concat(results)
2016            except Exception as e:
2017                PumpWoodException(message=str(e))
2018            print("\n## Finished parallel flat list: %s" % len(pool_arguments))
2019
2020        ############################################
2021        # If table have partition, run in parallel #
2022        else:
2023            try:
2024                results_key_data = self._flat_list_by_chunks_helper({
2025                    "model_class": model_class,
2026                    "filter_dict": temp_filter_dict,
2027                    "exclude_dict": exclude_dict,
2028                    "fields": fields,
2029                    "show_deleted": show_deleted,
2030                    "auth_header": auth_header,
2031                    "chunk_size": chunk_size})
2032                resp_df = results_key_data
2033            except Exception as e:
2034                PumpWoodException(message=str(e))
2035
2036        if (1 < len(partition)) and create_composite_pk:
2037            print("## Creating composite pk")
2038            resp_df["pk"] = resp_df[primary_keys].apply(
2039                CompositePkBase64Converter.dump,
2040                primary_keys=primary_keys, axis=1)
2041        return resp_df

def parallel_execute_action( self, model_class: Union[str, List[str]], pk: Union[int, List[int]], action: Union[str, List[str]], parameters: Union[dict, List[dict]] = {}, n_parallel: int = None, auth_header: dict = None): 
2576    def parallel_execute_action(self, model_class: Union[str, List[str]],
2577                                pk: Union[int, List[int]],
2578                                action: Union[str, List[str]],
2579                                parameters: Union[dict, List[dict]] = {},
2580                                n_parallel: int = None,
2581                                auth_header: dict = None):
2582        """
2583        Make many [n_parallel] execute_action requests.
2584
2585        Args:
2586            model_class (str, list(str)): Model Class to perform action over,
2587                or a list of model class o make diferent actions.
2588            pk (int, list[int]): A list of the pks to perform action or a
2589                single pk to perform action with different paraemters.
2590            action (str, list[str]): A list of actions to perform or a single
2591                action to perform over all pks and parameters.
2592        Kwargs:
2593            parameters (dict, list[dict]): Parameters used to perform actions
2594                or a single dict to be used in all actions.
2595            n_parallel (int): Number of simultaneus get requests, if not set
2596                get from PUMPWOOD_COMUNICATION__N_PARALLEL env variable, if
2597                not set then 4 will be considered.
2598            auth_header(dict): Dictionary containing the auth header.
2599        Returns:
2600            list: List of the retrieve request reponses.
2601        Raises:
2602            No particular raises
2603        Example:
2604            No example yet.
2605
2606        """
2607        if n_parallel is None:
2608            n_parallel = int(os.getenv(
2609                "PUMPWOOD_COMUNICATION__N_PARALLEL", 4))
2610
2611        parallel_length = None
2612        if type(model_class) == list:
2613            if parallel_length is not None:
2614                if parallel_length != len(model_class):
2615                    raise Exception('parallel_length != len(model_class)')
2616            else:
2617                parallel_length = len(model_class)
2618        if type(pk) == list:
2619            if parallel_length is not None:
2620                if parallel_length != len(pk):
2621                    raise Exception('parallel_length != len(pk)')
2622            else:
2623                parallel_length = len(pk)
2624        if type(action) == list:
2625            if parallel_length is not None:
2626                if parallel_length != len(action):
2627                    raise Exception('parallel_length != len(action)')
2628            else:
2629                parallel_length = len(action)
2630        if type(parameters) == list:
2631            if parallel_length is not None:
2632                if parallel_length != len(parameters):
2633                    raise Exception('parallel_length != len(parameters)')
2634            else:
2635                parallel_length = len(parameters)
2636
2637        model_class = model_class if type(model_class) == list \
2638            else [model_class]*parallel_length
2639        pk = pk if type(pk) == list \
2640            else [pk]*parallel_length
2641        action = action if type(action) == list \
2642            else [action]*parallel_length
2643        parameters = parameters if type(parameters) == list \
2644            else [parameters]*parallel_length
2645
2646        urls_list = [
2647            self._build_execute_action_url(
2648                model_class=model_class[i], action=action[i], pk=pk[i])
2649            for i in range(parallel_length)]
2650
2651        print("## Starting parallel_execute_action: %s" % len(urls_list))
2652        return self.paralell_request_post(
2653            urls_list=urls_list, data_list=parameters,
2654            n_parallel=n_parallel, auth_header=auth_header)
